2
00:00:28.396 --> 00:00:30.140
Now. let me just
get this straight.

3
00:00:30.164 --> 00:00:32.776
You're telling me that today is the
only day we can have this meeting.

4
00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:34.111
which happens to
be Christmas Eve

5
00:00:34.135 --> 00:00:35.579
and also my daughter's
birthday. thank you very much.

6
00:00:35.603 --> 00:00:37.481
Let's play geography.
California.

7
00:00:37.505 --> 00:00:39.549
Arkansas. Arkansas?

8
00:00:39.573 --> 00:00:41.251
Does that end with
an "A" or a "W"?

9
00:00:41.275 --> 00:00:42.310
An "S."

10
00:00:43.144 --> 00:00:44.754
Saudi Arabian Desert.

11
00:00:44.778 --> 00:00:46.823
You already used Saudi Arabia.

12
00:00:46.847 --> 00:00:48.382
Not the desert.

13
00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:58.235
What's going on?

14
00:00:58.259 --> 00:01:01.571
Timbuktu. Okay. you
just made that up.

15
00:01:01.595 --> 00:01:03.173
I did not. It's a real place.

16
00:01:03.197 --> 00:01:04.341
Fine.

17
00:01:04.365 --> 00:01:06.400
"U". "U..." What
starts with "U"?

18
00:01:07.668 --> 00:01:10.247
Up. Up? Up isn't a place.

19
00:01:10.271 --> 00:01:11.305
Yes. it is.

20
00:01:12.473 --> 00:01:13.974
It's up there.

21
00:01:14.975 --> 00:01:16.410
You're such a dork.

22
00:01:28.589 --> 00:01:29.723
That's better.

23
00:01:54.648 --> 00:01:56.693
What's their story?

24
00:01:56.717 --> 00:01:58.928
Those poor boys.

25
00:01:58.952 --> 00:02:01.064
The woman. Annie Binkow.

26
00:02:01.088 --> 00:02:04.734
is the owner of the traveling
circus where the boys work.

27
00:02:04.758 --> 00:02:06.870
Their mother is the fat lady.

28
00:02:06.894 --> 00:02:10.106
and their father swallows
swords and tames lions.

29
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:13.977
Name of the circus? Annie's
Big Top Spectacular

30
00:02:14.001 --> 00:02:16.103
and Lion Extravaganza.

31
00:02:17.538 --> 00:02:21.218
The performers are forced
to entertain alien children

32
00:02:21.242 --> 00:02:25.822
who have three heads
and six feet.

33
00:02:25.846 --> 00:02:28.425
And aliens don't applaud
like us. you know.

34
00:02:28.449 --> 00:02:30.418
What do they do instead?
They tap dance.

35
00:02:32.853 --> 00:02:34.622
Coolest story ever.

36
00:02:40.628 --> 00:02:44.441
Well. that was a
total waste of time.

37
00:02:44.465 --> 00:02:48.312
They actually wanted me to mount a
musical about teenage vampires.

38
00:02:48.336 --> 00:02:51.715
I mean. who in their right mind
wants to go to the theater

39
00:02:51.739 --> 00:02:53.241
and watch a lot of
singing vampires?

40
00:02:53.941 --> 00:02:55.652
(BOTH LAUGH)

41
00:02:55.676 --> 00:02:58.121
Well. that looks like it
must've been delicious.

42
00:02:58.145 --> 00:02:59.723
I didn't eat it all by myself.

43
00:02:59.747 --> 00:03:01.891
We shared it.

44
00:03:01.915 --> 00:03:05.128
Well. honey. I think maybe
you've had enough. Time to go.

45
00:03:05.152 --> 00:03:07.255
But we're celebrating my birthday.
Thank you.

46
00:03:08.589 --> 00:03:11.325
Hurry up. We've certainly
spent enough time here.

47
00:03:14.728 --> 00:03:16.440
Are you okay?

48
00:03:16.464 --> 00:03:18.675
Remember when I was little

49
00:03:18.699 --> 00:03:22.069
and I thought if I closed my
eyes that nobody could see me?

50
00:03:22.570 --> 00:03:23.637
Yeah.

51
00:03:24.605 --> 00:03:25.839
I wish I still believed that.

52
00:03:31.279 --> 00:03:34.715
Don't look now. but I see the prettiest
girl I've ever seen in my whole life.

53
00:03:35.716 --> 00:03:37.060
Where?

54
00:03:37.084 --> 00:03:39.529
To your left. but
don't look too fast.

55
00:03:39.553 --> 00:03:42.155
I bet she's pretty tired of people
staring at her all the time.

56
00:03:42.656 --> 00:03:43.757
A little more.

57
00:03:46.394 --> 00:03:47.928
A little more.

58
00:04:01.375 --> 00:04:04.754
Do you know why we get your birthday
present at Tiffany's every year?

59
00:04:04.778 --> 00:04:06.189
Because it's our favorite store.

60
00:04:06.213 --> 00:04:09.959
and a girl should never depend
on a man to buy her jewelry.

61
00:04:09.983 --> 00:04:13.530
Quite right. You are the only person
you can count on in this world.

62
00:04:13.554 --> 00:04:17.301
What people call true love is only
for fairytales and greeting cards.

63
00:04:17.325 --> 00:04:18.968
She's wrong.

64
00:04:18.992 --> 00:04:22.772
Real love. true love lasts forever
and ever. It never goes away.

65
00:04:22.796 --> 00:04:25.032
Come on. let's go get
something gorgeous.

66
00:04:39.012 --> 00:04:41.048
It's beautiful. I know.

67
00:04:43.417 --> 00:04:44.552
Look at that diamond.

68
00:04:47.521 --> 00:04:49.390
It sparkles so much.

69
00:04:50.758 --> 00:04:52.502
Look at that big one.

70
00:04:52.526 --> 00:04:54.738
Excuse me. sir.
Do you work here?

71
00:04:54.762 --> 00:04:58.274
I'm looking for the most beautiful
jewelry in the entire store.

72
00:04:58.298 --> 00:05:02.111
Can you help me? Okay. that's great.
Show me everything you have.

73
00:05:02.135 --> 00:05:04.472
Come on. let's go see over here.

74
00:05:05.839 --> 00:05:07.917
Look at that. Look
at that. Michael.

75
00:05:07.941 --> 00:05:09.252
It's so yellow.

76
00:05:09.276 --> 00:05:11.821
It's so me. Would you
like to try something on?

77
00:05:11.845 --> 00:05:15.859
Yes. please. I'd like that one.

78
00:05:15.883 --> 00:05:17.084
Wonderful choice.

79
00:05:18.118 --> 00:05:19.219
Okay.

80
00:05:23.757 --> 00:05:25.225
There you go.

81
00:05:27.194 --> 00:05:28.896
It's so beautiful.

82
00:05:32.833 --> 00:05:34.644
She's gonna love this.

83
00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:38.948
Yes. I love it. Don't you. Michael?
It's so beautiful.

84
00:05:38.972 --> 00:05:40.950
Your daughter is so imaginative.

85
00:05:40.974 --> 00:05:44.177
We're a very theatrical family.
It's so yellow and pretty.

86
00:05:45.413 --> 00:05:46.856
Shall I wrap it up for you?

87
00:05:46.880 --> 00:05:47.948
I wish.

88
00:05:51.284 --> 00:05:54.263
When you grow up and get married.
that will be your wedding ring.

89
00:05:54.287 --> 00:05:56.927
It's yellow. You're supposed to wear
a diamond when you get married.

90
00:05:56.951 --> 00:06:00.404
That's the rule. Some rules
were made to be broken.

91
00:06:00.428 --> 00:06:04.508
You should have a ring that tells the
world you are Jane. You're special.

92
00:06:04.532 --> 00:06:06.333
That's a yellow diamond.
It's very special.

93
00:06:08.135 --> 00:06:11.204
Perfect. In that case.
it really is your ring.

94
00:06:15.409 --> 00:06:18.755
It's almost 5:15. I'll
be double digits.

95
00:06:18.779 --> 00:06:22.058
Ten years old. The
age of awareness.

96
00:06:22.082 --> 00:06:26.930
The year you start making your
own decisions. The year you...

97
00:06:26.954 --> 00:06:29.198
The year you start to let
go of your childhood.

98
00:06:29.222 --> 00:06:31.768
What are you talking about?

99
00:06:31.792 --> 00:06:35.071
You're ready to stand
on your own two feet.

100
00:06:35.095 --> 00:06:37.273
It's time for me to go.

101
00:06:37.297 --> 00:06:38.566
Go where?

102
00:06:40.333 --> 00:06:44.481
I'm going to have to leave at
5:15. the moment you were born.

103
00:06:44.505 --> 00:06:45.639
What?

104
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:48.308
Why? For how long?

105
00:06:50.744 --> 00:06:51.979
Forever.

106
00:06:54.147 --> 00:06:56.359
No. you can't do that.

107
00:06:56.383 --> 00:06:59.295
We're only allowed to stay
until our child turns 10.

108
00:06:59.319 --> 00:07:02.766
After that. all imaginary
friends have to leave.

109
00:07:02.790 --> 00:07:04.634
That's not fair.

110
00:07:04.658 --> 00:07:09.172
You'll be okay. You're smart
and creative and strong.

111
00:07:09.196 --> 00:07:11.240
Why didn't you tell me
this was gonna happen?

112
00:07:11.264 --> 00:07:17.280
I tried. I looked for the perfect moment.
It just never seemed to be the right time.

113
00:07:17.304 --> 00:07:20.450
I won't let you leave.
I forbid it.

114
00:07:20.474 --> 00:07:22.752
I don't have a choice.
It's the rules.

115
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.588
You said rules were
made to be broken.

116
00:07:24.612 --> 00:07:25.822
Not this one.

117
00:07:25.846 --> 00:07:27.156
I want to come with you.

118
00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:29.025
You can't.

119
00:07:29.049 --> 00:07:33.196
This is the first place we met. so this
is the place we have to say goodbye.

120
00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:34.831
But I'll miss you too much.

121
00:07:34.855 --> 00:07:37.066
After I'm gone. you
won't even remember me.

122
00:07:37.090 --> 00:07:40.403
But you're the only one who
knows everything about me.

123
00:07:40.427 --> 00:07:43.230
You're my best friend
in the whole world.

124
00:07:45.999 --> 00:07:47.367
I love you.

125
00:07:49.136 --> 00:07:50.647
I love you. too.

126
00:07:50.671 --> 00:07:52.849
You're crying.

127
00:07:52.873 --> 00:07:54.107
I've never seen you cry.

128
00:07:55.408 --> 00:07:56.510
I am?

129
00:08:11.424 --> 00:08:14.995
You're in my heart. Love
is never being apart.

130
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:19.299
Michael! Michael! Michael!
Michael!

131
00:08:20.267 --> 00:08:21.501
Michael!

132
00:08:23.804 --> 00:08:25.615
Wait! Open! Hey. what is it?

133
00:08:25.639 --> 00:08:26.850
Open the door. please! I
have to get something!

134
00:08:26.874 --> 00:08:28.718
What's wrong?
Michael's in there!

135
00:08:28.742 --> 00:08:30.920
Your son? No. no. no. It's
nothing. it's nothing.

136
00:08:30.944 --> 00:08:32.321
It's just her imaginary friend.

137
00:08:32.345 --> 00:08:35.182
No! He's real! He's in there!

138
00:08:35.949 --> 00:08:37.426
Look.

139
00:08:37.450 --> 00:08:41.798
There he is. There's your little friend.
Hi. Michael.

140
00:08:41.822 --> 00:08:45.025
He's gone. and he's
never coming back.

141
00:08:46.927 --> 00:08:48.905
Look what I got you.

142
00:08:48.929 --> 00:08:52.776
I got you this beautiful necklace
that you can wear forever.

143
00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:56.880
Now. maybe this is for the best.

144
00:08:56.904 --> 00:08:59.306
Maybe you don't
need him anymore.

145
00:09:00.808 --> 00:09:02.710
I do need you. Michael.

146
00:09:32.940 --> 00:09:34.041
Jane!

147
00:09:37.010 --> 00:09:38.855
I know.

148
00:09:38.879 --> 00:09:41.414
Jane. what are you
doing over there?

149
00:09:42.382 --> 00:09:43.851
Get over here.

150
00:09:47.187 --> 00:09:48.798
It's vintage. I love it.

151
00:09:48.822 --> 00:09:50.299
Do you want to borrow
my wedding dress?

152
00:09:50.323 --> 00:09:52.403
That is very sweet. but I've
got things under control.

153
00:09:52.427 --> 00:09:54.107
Really? That's not what
you said last week.

154
00:09:54.995 --> 00:09:57.340
I can't believe you're marrying Dr.
Sellars.

155
00:09:57.364 --> 00:09:59.075
He's not Dr. Sellars anymore.

156
00:09:59.099 --> 00:10:01.044
He'll always be Dr.
Sellars to me.

157
00:10:01.068 --> 00:10:04.881
Every Tuesday night.
9:00. the doctor was in.

158
00:10:04.905 --> 00:10:09.076
These are presents for my
beautiful bridesmaids.

159
00:10:10.911 --> 00:10:14.023
I hope you like them.
It's beautiful.

160
00:10:14.047 --> 00:10:16.884
Okay. Let's get this party started.
Do it.

161
00:10:17.685 --> 00:10:18.919
Tequila.

162
00:10:20.854 --> 00:10:22.866
To Jane. ALL: To Jane.

163
00:10:22.890 --> 00:10:24.524
And Hugh. ALL: And Hugh.

164
00:10:33.133 --> 00:10:34.835
(PHONE RINGING)

165
00:10:36.603 --> 00:10:38.281
(ANSWERING MACHINE TONE)

166
00:10:38.305 --> 00:10:40.705
Hey. Jane. don't forget to watch
me on Good Morning. New York.

167
00:10:40.729 --> 00:10:44.566
I go on at 9:30 or something.
I'll meet you after. Love you.

168
00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:10.914
I went to see your play
Barrymore Speaks last week.

169
00:11:10.938 --> 00:11:13.649
and I have to say I
thoroughly enjoyed it.

170
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:18.154
Thank you. Yeah. the theater
is a new medium for me and...

171
00:11:18.178 --> 00:11:20.156
But I had great
material to work with.

172
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:24.160
And being so close to the audience and
feeling their immediate response.

173
00:11:24.184 --> 00:11:26.095
it's intoxicating.

174
00:11:26.119 --> 00:11:30.233
Now. so many people still think of you
as cardiac surgeon Dr. Mark Sellars

175
00:11:30.257 --> 00:11:33.569
from the hit primetime
series Emergency Heights.

176
00:11:33.593 --> 00:11:36.305
(APPLAUSE) Thank you.
Thank you. Wow.

177
00:11:36.329 --> 00:11:41.277
Does that bother you at all?
How could it?

178
00:11:41.301 --> 00:11:45.815
It was a great role to play and
it's in reruns all over the world.

179
00:11:45.839 --> 00:11:47.116
(ANSWERING MACHINE TONE)

180
00:11:47.140 --> 00:11:50.519
Hello. dear. It's your mother.
Just a gentle reminder.

181
00:11:50.543 --> 00:11:54.223
I just think it's astonishing that you
haven't finished planning your wedding.

182
00:11:54.247 --> 00:11:57.861
A wedding. I might add. that will
take place in less than 30 days.

183
00:11:57.885 --> 00:12:01.164
There's a surprise on Page Six for
you this morning. You're welcome.

184
00:12:01.188 --> 00:12:03.032
Do you know what they
call it in Hong Kong?

185
00:12:03.056 --> 00:12:05.568
(SPEAKING CANTONESE)

186
00:12:05.592 --> 00:12:07.636
Do you know what that means?
INTERVIEWER: No.

187
00:12:07.660 --> 00:12:11.107
Well. it means "very
handsome doctor."

188
00:12:11.131 --> 00:12:13.476
This is Jane Claremont again.

189
00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:17.446
My shower still isn't working.
so I would really appreciate it

190
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:20.283
if you could stop by and
take a look at it. okay?

191
00:12:20.307 --> 00:12:22.585
And if I don't hear
from you this time.

192
00:12:22.609 --> 00:12:28.624
I will be forced to lodge a
complaint with the plumbers' union

193
00:12:28.648 --> 00:12:32.395
or the Better Business Bureau.
Okay. thanks so much. Bye.

194
00:12:32.419 --> 00:12:36.032
Hello. sweetheart. Hello. Mrs.
Greenberg. Hello. Coco.

195
00:12:36.056 --> 00:12:38.567
I am gonna pick up treats
for you on the way home.

196
00:12:38.591 --> 00:12:40.403
That's so sweet of you. dear.

197
00:12:40.427 --> 00:12:43.139
Without them. he gets
anxious and despondent.

198
00:12:43.163 --> 00:12:46.433
I know he does. Okay. have a great day.
You. too.

199
00:12:49.469 --> 00:12:52.315
Good morning.
beautiful neighbor.

200
00:12:52.339 --> 00:12:54.017
Thank you.

201
00:12:54.041 --> 00:12:58.554
Fifteen. 17. 19. 21. 28.

202
00:12:58.578 --> 00:13:01.457
Bonus number is 24.
You remembered.

203
00:13:01.481 --> 00:13:04.660
Well. you play the same numbers every week.
All of your wives' birthdays.

204
00:13:04.684 --> 00:13:07.520
And I got lucky
with all of them.

205
00:13:09.556 --> 00:13:11.734
You've written an autobiography.
Yes.

206
00:13:11.758 --> 00:13:13.702
It's about to be released.

207
00:13:13.726 --> 00:13:15.604
Now. you're so young.

208
00:13:15.628 --> 00:13:19.666
What made you decide to write
about your life at this point?

209
00:13:21.835 --> 00:13:25.148
I feel like I'm several
chapters into my life now.

210
00:13:25.172 --> 00:13:30.153
and I wanted to put down on
paper the me that I've been

211
00:13:30.177 --> 00:13:33.156
on the way to becoming
the me I'll be.

212
00:13:33.180 --> 00:13:35.983
One last thing before I let you go.
Okay.

213
00:13:36.850 --> 00:13:38.294
You're engaged. Yes.

214
00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:41.931
You proposed to your fiancee.
Jane Claremont. live

215
00:13:41.955 --> 00:13:45.334
on The Tonight Show
six months ago.

216
00:13:45.358 --> 00:13:49.038
Was that planned? Was it a
spur of the moment thing?

217
00:13:49.062 --> 00:13:52.842
Meredith. if being in love is
something that can be planned.

218
00:13:52.866 --> 00:13:55.068
then. yes. it was
spur of the moment.

219
00:14:12.752 --> 00:14:15.598
Good morning. Mrs. Morrison.
It's ready.

220
00:14:15.622 --> 00:14:17.925
I'm not Mrs. Morrison just yet.

221
00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:22.605
It's so beautiful.

222
00:14:22.629 --> 00:14:24.607
Thank you so much for
getting it done so fast.

223
00:14:24.631 --> 00:14:26.266
My pleasure.

224
00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:30.046
So what's it like? Excuse me?

225
00:14:30.070 --> 00:14:32.581
What's it like being
engaged to Hugh Morrison?

226
00:14:32.605 --> 00:14:35.184
Is he just like Dr. Sellars
on Emergency Heights?

227
00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:38.687
So romantic. He's your
soul mate. isn't he?

228
00:14:38.711 --> 00:14:41.224
Your one true love? The
man that completes you?

229
00:14:41.248 --> 00:14:44.811
Well. yeah. I mean. I
guess. if there is such

230
00:14:44.823 --> 00:14:48.397
a thing as a soul mate.
he would be mine.

231
00:14:48.421 --> 00:14:50.924
Thank you so much.
You're welcome.

232
00:15:32.499 --> 00:15:33.943
(CAR SCREECHING AND HONKING)

233
00:15:33.967 --> 00:15:35.778
Hey! What are you doing?

234
00:15:35.802 --> 00:15:37.046
(CAR HONKING)

235
00:15:37.070 --> 00:15:38.514
Come on!

236
00:15:38.538 --> 00:15:40.583
Get out of the street!

237
00:15:40.607 --> 00:15:42.485
Are you talking to me?

238
00:15:42.509 --> 00:15:44.253
Yeah. I'm talking to you! I don't
see anyone else standing there!

239
00:15:44.277 --> 00:15:45.388
You can see me?

240
00:15:45.412 --> 00:15:47.023
Yeah. I can see you. nut job!

241
00:15:47.047 --> 00:15:49.558
Come on! Get the hell out of the way!
Move it!

242
00:15:49.582 --> 00:15:51.684
Rockefeller Center. please.

243
00:16:06.933 --> 00:16:10.046
Be totally honest. How was I?
Are you kidding?

244
00:16:10.070 --> 00:16:13.649
I thought Meredith was gonna
jump over and sit in your lap.

245
00:16:13.673 --> 00:16:15.518
You were wonderful.

246
00:16:15.542 --> 00:16:18.654
Dr. Sellars. Why do they always
bring up ancient history?

247
00:16:18.678 --> 00:16:20.856
Why can't they just
focus on my new work?

248
00:16:20.880 --> 00:16:22.658
She talked about the
book and the play.

249
00:16:22.682 --> 00:16:23.759
Yeah. I know. but...

250
00:16:23.783 --> 00:16:25.152
Look. Wow.

251
00:16:25.818 --> 00:16:26.962
I got it sized.

252
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.531
That is a beautiful ring. Yeah.

253
00:16:28.555 --> 00:16:30.890
Someone must love you very much.

254
00:16:34.394 --> 00:16:38.007
See us on Page Six? I know.
I'm sorry.

255
00:16:38.031 --> 00:16:41.077
My mother loves to use you for
publicity for the theater.

256
00:16:41.101 --> 00:16:42.845
No. I think it's cute.

257
00:16:42.869 --> 00:16:44.947
Speaking of my book. Little.
Brown Publishing called.

258
00:16:44.971 --> 00:16:48.117
They want me to read an excerpt of it
before the signing at Barnes & Noble.

259
00:16:48.141 --> 00:16:49.909
That's so exciting.
I know. right?

260
00:16:50.510 --> 00:16:52.155
(SHIVERS)

261
00:16:52.179 --> 00:16:54.659
Honey. I told you to wear a heavier coat.
You're gonna get sick.

262
00:16:54.683 --> 00:16:55.984
I know. I know.

263
00:16:56.816 --> 00:16:58.627
Okay. I have to go
to the theater.

264
00:16:58.651 --> 00:17:00.863
How are the wedding plans going?
Almost done.

265
00:17:00.887 --> 00:17:05.101
Good. Everything's gonna be perfect.
I can't wait to make you my wife.

266
00:17:05.125 --> 00:17:06.759
I love you. Bye. Love you more.

267
00:17:12.465 --> 00:17:15.178
You did this? You're welcome.

268
00:17:15.202 --> 00:17:17.446
I still have a few
connections with the press.

269
00:17:17.470 --> 00:17:20.049
What makes you think that I
want a picture of me and Hugh

270
00:17:20.073 --> 00:17:21.350
kissing in the newspaper?

271
00:17:21.374 --> 00:17:23.152
We need all the
publicity we can get.

272
00:17:23.176 --> 00:17:25.188
We're sold out until the
end of the run. I know.

273
00:17:25.212 --> 00:17:26.955
Isn't it wonderful?

274
00:17:26.979 --> 00:17:30.826
You know. I was thinking. maybe we
should just extend for six weeks.

275
00:17:30.850 --> 00:17:33.696
taking a break for the wedding
and the honeymoon and all that.

276
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:36.165
and then come back in January
for a really limited run.

277
00:17:36.189 --> 00:17:40.002
I think that Hugh made it very clear
that he wants to be available for films.

278
00:17:40.026 --> 00:17:41.604
Well. we'll just have
to take that risk.

279
00:17:41.628 --> 00:17:44.273
I mean. if he gets a movie.
we'll hire someone else.

280
00:17:44.297 --> 00:17:47.700
Does George Clooney do stage?
Oh. my God!

281
00:17:48.735 --> 00:17:50.370
You've got the ring.

282
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:52.572
It's stunning.

283
00:17:54.407 --> 00:17:58.121
Tell me you found the dress.
I found the dress.

284
00:17:58.145 --> 00:18:02.825
I really think that the
Vera Wang was perfect.

285
00:18:02.849 --> 00:18:07.563
Fact. Cameron Diaz actually tried it on.
Rumor. she's engaged.

286
00:18:07.587 --> 00:18:11.224
Question. I heard that she dated
Hugh Morrison a couple years ago.

287
00:18:12.325 --> 00:18:14.270
I'll ask him and
get back to you.

288
00:18:14.294 --> 00:18:18.141
Statement. my mom and I love him. You
are so lucky to be marrying him.

289
00:18:18.165 --> 00:18:21.210
I like it. It's just. there's
something that's not right about it.

290
00:18:21.234 --> 00:18:22.645
and it has to be perfect.

291
00:18:22.669 --> 00:18:26.582
I know. You've tried every dress
on in the salon. three times.

292
00:18:26.606 --> 00:18:28.851
I know. I'm sorry. I just...
I can't decide.

293
00:18:28.875 --> 00:18:31.387
No. I'm sorry. My lunch
hour's only so long

294
00:18:31.411 --> 00:18:34.723
and my next patient is 15 and
still dresses like SpiderMan.

295
00:18:34.747 --> 00:18:36.459
I gotta go. Good luck.

296
00:18:36.483 --> 00:18:38.117
Thanks. You. too.

297
00:18:53.866 --> 00:18:55.144
Hi. Jane?

298
00:18:55.168 --> 00:18:56.269
Yeah.

299
00:18:57.437 --> 00:18:59.582
I'm sorry. Have we met before?

300
00:18:59.606 --> 00:19:03.051
No one ever remembers
me after I leave.

301
00:19:03.075 --> 00:19:05.388
Wait a minute. Was it at the...
The thing last week...

302
00:19:05.412 --> 00:19:07.523
We were best friends when
you were a little girl.

303
00:19:07.547 --> 00:19:11.460
So we went to school together?
Yeah. I went with you every day.

304
00:19:11.484 --> 00:19:13.362
I helped you study. We...

305
00:19:13.386 --> 00:19:17.733
Long division was a nightmare for me
always. but you always got it right away.

306
00:19:17.757 --> 00:19:20.403
Okay. we made a volcano
out of clay one time.

307
00:19:20.427 --> 00:19:22.238
And we put dry ice.

308
00:19:22.262 --> 00:19:25.608
and we put Pop Rocks inside of it. and
it erupted all over the classroom.

309
00:19:25.632 --> 00:19:31.247
And Mr. Lee. he choked on his coffee
and it came shooting out of his nose.

310
00:19:31.271 --> 00:19:33.105
Wow. it's so great
to see you again.

311
00:19:34.841 --> 00:19:38.144
Yeah. it's great
to see you again.

312
00:19:42.849 --> 00:19:45.027
Jacqueline. I'm telling
you. I've seen him twice

313
00:19:45.051 --> 00:19:47.396
in different parts of the
city and now he's here.

314
00:19:47.420 --> 00:19:49.232
The guy is definitely
stalking me.

315
00:19:49.256 --> 00:19:53.802
Stalking you? Are you sure? It's
probably just a coincidence.

316
00:19:53.826 --> 00:19:54.894
Is he cute?

317
00:19:57.764 --> 00:19:59.975
Well. yeah. but what
difference does that make?

318
00:19:59.999 --> 00:20:02.535
I mean. Ted Bundy was
kind of cute. right?

319
00:20:05.037 --> 00:20:07.983
Okay. he's gone. All right.

320
00:20:08.007 --> 00:20:10.377
Yeah. I know. It's so weird.

321
00:20:11.878 --> 00:20:15.824
Jane... Got to go. Why
are you following me?

322
00:20:15.848 --> 00:20:17.660
Answer me right now.
or I will mace you.

323
00:20:17.684 --> 00:20:20.062
That's a PEZ dispenser.
You still love candy.

324
00:20:20.086 --> 00:20:22.798
Do you remember freezing Milk Duds
and melting them in hot milk?

325
00:20:22.822 --> 00:20:25.167
It's the best. Why are you here?

326
00:20:25.191 --> 00:20:27.970
I don't know. I only can assume
it's because you need me.

327
00:20:27.994 --> 00:20:29.938
So what's wrong? How
can I help you. Jane?

328
00:20:29.962 --> 00:20:33.476
No. no. no. I can assure you
that I do not need you.

329
00:20:33.500 --> 00:20:35.711
And if you don't leave me
alone. I'm calling 911.

330
00:20:35.735 --> 00:20:39.615
Do you remember when we called 911
because your goldfish Charlie died?

331
00:20:39.639 --> 00:20:42.851
Paramedics were not happy.
How did you know that?

332
00:20:42.875 --> 00:20:44.553
I... No.

333
00:20:44.577 --> 00:20:45.954
Don't answer that. because I
want you to leave me alone.

334
00:20:45.978 --> 00:20:48.257
You've grown into a
beautiful woman. Jane.

335
00:20:48.281 --> 00:20:50.092
That's it. I am
calling the police.

336
00:20:50.116 --> 00:20:53.396
Jane. Jane. it's me.

337
00:20:53.420 --> 00:20:57.165
Your imaginary friend from age
five and threequarters to 10.

338
00:20:57.189 --> 00:21:01.003
Yes. well. am I being punk'd right now?
Because this is weird.

339
00:21:01.027 --> 00:21:03.171
Are there hidden cameras?
Is this a reality show?

340
00:21:03.195 --> 00:21:06.208
Listen. the carousel in Central Park.
You always had to have the pink pony.

341
00:21:06.232 --> 00:21:07.912
What little girl didn't
want the pink pony?

342
00:21:07.936 --> 00:21:09.571
I always rode behind you.

343
00:21:13.540 --> 00:21:14.641
Stay!

344
00:21:18.077 --> 00:21:20.155
What's wrong with you?

345
00:21:20.179 --> 00:21:22.224
I'm not sure. You?

346
00:21:22.248 --> 00:21:26.562
My mother says I'm
depressed and delusional.

347
00:21:26.586 --> 00:21:28.921
My mother used to tell
me the same thing.

348
00:21:29.822 --> 00:21:31.090
BOTH: Mothers.

349
00:21:34.327 --> 00:21:36.271
I'll just be one second.

350
00:21:36.295 --> 00:21:37.664
Okay. Okay.

351
00:21:40.965 --> 00:21:42.445
What are you doing here?
Are you okay?

352
00:21:42.469 --> 00:21:43.770
I'm having a mental breakdown.

353
00:21:46.138 --> 00:21:48.884
Just choose a wedding dress.
You'll feel better.

354
00:21:48.908 --> 00:21:52.388
I'm being followed by a
figment of my imagination.

355
00:21:52.412 --> 00:21:54.222
That stalker you
called me about?

356
00:21:54.246 --> 00:21:57.125
He says he's my imaginary friend
from when I was a little girl.

357
00:21:57.149 --> 00:22:01.597
The thing is. I actually had an
imaginary friend when I was little.

358
00:22:01.621 --> 00:22:05.324
And there are things about my childhood.
things that there's no way he could know.

359
00:22:06.826 --> 00:22:09.204
He probably found
you on Facebook.

360
00:22:09.228 --> 00:22:12.164
I bet he's an actor. He just
wants a part in your new play.

361
00:22:13.733 --> 00:22:16.335
You know what? You're
probably right.

362
00:22:18.438 --> 00:22:19.539
Okay.

363
00:22:20.673 --> 00:22:22.685
So how are the
wedding plans going?

364
00:22:22.709 --> 00:22:26.088
I can't seem to make any decisions.
Nothing is perfect.

365
00:22:26.112 --> 00:22:28.156
That's because
nothing is perfect.

366
00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:31.226
You just have to find something
you like and buy it.

367
00:22:31.250 --> 00:22:34.029
I can't. It's too hard.

368
00:22:34.053 --> 00:22:37.032
You know what they say about people
who can't make the little decisions

369
00:22:37.056 --> 00:22:39.067
leading up to the big decision?

370
00:22:39.091 --> 00:22:42.571
Please don't start this again.
Hugh is perfect for me.

371
00:22:42.595 --> 00:22:44.607
You've only known him a year.

372
00:22:44.631 --> 00:22:47.111
He proposed to you on latenight television.
You couldn't say no.

373
00:22:47.135 --> 00:22:49.878
I didn't wanna say no.
I love him.

374
00:22:49.902 --> 00:22:52.247
Okay. okay.

375
00:22:52.271 --> 00:22:55.451
I have to see my next patient.
You'd like him.

376
00:22:55.475 --> 00:22:58.320
He arrives with an invisible
four-foot tall rabbit named Paul.

377
00:22:58.344 --> 00:23:00.547
Very funny. Very funny.

378
00:23:09.522 --> 00:23:11.090
Bye. Bye.

379
00:23:19.732 --> 00:23:21.076
Jane.

380
00:23:21.100 --> 00:23:24.079
Oh. my God. You have got
to stop following me.

381
00:23:24.103 --> 00:23:27.883
If you're an actor and you want an audition.
have your agent call the theater.

382
00:23:27.907 --> 00:23:29.747
I don't have an agent.
Well. you should get one

383
00:23:29.771 --> 00:23:31.119
because you are freaking me out.

384
00:23:31.143 --> 00:23:32.688
I'm freaked out. too. okay?

385
00:23:32.712 --> 00:23:34.993
I've never been freaked out
before. so imagine my surprise.

386
00:23:35.017 --> 00:23:36.857
Jane. Jane. I need you
to help me figure out...

387
00:23:36.881 --> 00:23:41.329
Enough. enough. enough. enough.
You've got to stop following me.

388
00:23:41.353 --> 00:23:46.334
I left you on your 10th birthday
at 5:15. the moment you were born.

389
00:23:46.358 --> 00:23:49.038
I told you I had to leave and you
cried when I got into the elevator.

390
00:23:53.866 --> 00:23:55.167
How did you know that?

391
00:23:57.269 --> 00:23:58.437
I'm Michael.

392
00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:02.008
Michael?

393
00:24:03.242 --> 00:24:04.443
Yeah.

394
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:13.352
What...

395
00:24:21.260 --> 00:24:23.171
Did that hurt?

396
00:24:23.195 --> 00:24:27.810
If "hurt" means my face is on fire and my
eyes are watering. then. yeah. it hurt.

397
00:24:27.834 --> 00:24:29.745
I'm really sorry.

398
00:24:29.769 --> 00:24:34.216
It's just. you brought up
a painful memory for me.

399
00:24:34.240 --> 00:24:38.878
Michael broke my heart. I
cried for weeks when he left.

400
00:24:43.516 --> 00:24:45.293
How can you be Michael?

401
00:24:45.317 --> 00:24:47.996
I don't know. I'm just as surprised
that I'm here as you are.

402
00:24:48.020 --> 00:24:49.297
It just doesn't make sense.

403
00:24:49.321 --> 00:24:50.599
I know.

404
00:24:50.623 --> 00:24:52.467
I mean. I get that
when I was little.

405
00:24:52.491 --> 00:24:54.703
I was lonely and I needed
an imaginary friend.

406
00:24:54.727 --> 00:24:59.041
But now. my life is perfect.

407
00:24:59.065 --> 00:25:02.377
You know. I have a great
job. a great apartment.

408
00:25:02.401 --> 00:25:05.672
I'm engaged to a man that most
women would die to marry.

409
00:25:09.175 --> 00:25:13.079
And imaginary friends are imaginary.
So I got to go to work.

410
00:25:20.286 --> 00:25:23.532
What the hell.

411
00:25:23.556 --> 00:25:27.927
All right. catch me up. Tell me everything
that's happened to you since you were 10.

412
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:31.263
That's like 28 years.

413
00:25:32.298 --> 00:25:34.701
I don't know. I grew up.

414
00:25:35.835 --> 00:25:37.436
This is amazing.

415
00:25:38.170 --> 00:25:39.606
It's a donut.

416
00:25:42.508 --> 00:25:43.643
Hey.

417
00:25:45.645 --> 00:25:47.623
What's the story with those two?

418
00:25:47.647 --> 00:25:51.694
They're making snowflakes
for the holiday show.

419
00:25:51.718 --> 00:25:54.120
No. I mean. their secret lives.

420
00:25:54.921 --> 00:25:57.265
I don't really know them.

421
00:25:57.289 --> 00:25:59.892
You don't play the
story game anymore?

422
00:26:01.694 --> 00:26:07.610
No. No. no. I'm an adult now. I don't
really play any games anymore.

423
00:26:07.634 --> 00:26:11.814
You know. I have a job and a life
and places that I have to be.

424
00:26:11.838 --> 00:26:14.983
So. it was great
to see you again.

425
00:26:15.007 --> 00:26:20.079
Great in a delusional. out of my mind.
"hope to wake up soon" kind of way.

426
00:26:21.113 --> 00:26:23.449
I've missed your sense of humor.

427
00:26:25.084 --> 00:26:26.364
You know what? One
more question.

428
00:26:28.020 --> 00:26:31.166
Why didn't you become
a pastry chef?

429
00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:33.902
Or a writer? I chose
to manage a theater.

430
00:26:33.926 --> 00:26:36.271
Your mother's theater. Yeah.

431
00:26:36.295 --> 00:26:39.474
That wasn't your life's dream.
I was 10.

432
00:26:39.498 --> 00:26:41.818
People don't become what they
wanted to when they were kids.

433
00:26:41.842 --> 00:26:45.580
Otherwise. all little boys would be
firefighters or dump truck drivers.

434
00:26:45.604 --> 00:26:47.244
and all little girls
would become Madonna.

435
00:26:47.974 --> 00:26:49.084
I know. but it's...

436
00:26:49.108 --> 00:26:50.476
I grew up.

437
00:26:53.980 --> 00:26:56.348
I'm defending
myself to a mirage.

438
00:26:58.818 --> 00:27:01.830
I'm telling you. Peter. it's like
she doesn't believe in me anymore.

439
00:27:01.854 --> 00:27:03.966
She acts like she's scared
of me or something.

440
00:27:03.990 --> 00:27:08.303
Do you blame her? You scared me.
too. showing up all big and human.

441
00:27:08.327 --> 00:27:11.106
It still freaks me out a little.
I just don't understand.

442
00:27:11.130 --> 00:27:14.109
Me. neither. You know. it's like
I got a foot in both worlds.

443
00:27:14.133 --> 00:27:16.235
You see me. They see me.

444
00:27:18.805 --> 00:27:19.948
I'm really good at this.

445
00:27:19.972 --> 00:27:21.932
Of course you're good.
You're. like. 10 feet tall.

446
00:27:23.175 --> 00:27:25.187
So what do I do? I don't know.

447
00:27:25.211 --> 00:27:29.591
I guess you're just gonna have to ride
it out and wait for reassignment.

448
00:27:29.615 --> 00:27:33.285
It shouldn't be long. The way the world
is right now. we're spread pretty thin.

449
00:27:34.420 --> 00:27:36.765
So. when's her birthday?

450
00:27:36.789 --> 00:27:39.668
That's probably your exit date.
You think?

451
00:27:39.692 --> 00:27:43.939
You may be temporarily human.
but the rules are rules.

452
00:27:43.963 --> 00:27:47.009
We come when they need us. and
we leave on their birthdays.

453
00:27:47.033 --> 00:27:48.877
Her birthday's December 24.

454
00:27:48.901 --> 00:27:52.647
You better figure out what she needs
so you can get back to normal.

455
00:27:52.671 --> 00:27:54.316
Right.

456
00:27:54.340 --> 00:27:55.742
I got to go. Okay.

457
00:28:00.179 --> 00:28:03.158
He shows up and just
expects me to accept

458
00:28:03.182 --> 00:28:06.862
that he's like this imaginary ghost
from my childhood or something.

459
00:28:06.886 --> 00:28:08.797
I mean. that's crazy. right?

460
00:28:08.821 --> 00:28:11.433
I am a logical. rational person.

461
00:28:11.457 --> 00:28:15.670
I mean. I don't drink excessively. I
don't do drugs. I pay my taxes on time.

462
00:28:15.694 --> 00:28:19.942
I am obsessive about recycling.

463
00:28:19.966 --> 00:28:24.079
And part of me wants to believe
that it really is Michael.

464
00:28:24.103 --> 00:28:28.174
and then there's a part of me that just
thinks I should have myself committed.

465
00:28:30.209 --> 00:28:31.577
Do you think I'm losing my mind?

466
00:28:36.315 --> 00:28:39.561
So the producers loved the show tonight.
Maury called.

467
00:28:39.585 --> 00:28:41.396
He thinks I'm being
considered for the lead

468
00:28:41.408 --> 00:28:43.231
role in a feature film.
a romantic comedy.

469
00:28:43.255 --> 00:28:45.233
I always knew something
like this would happen.

470
00:28:45.257 --> 00:28:47.257
I mean. can you imagine
what this will mean for me?

471
00:28:47.281 --> 00:28:50.317
You get one lead role. the rest
just follows. and I'm back!

472
00:28:52.731 --> 00:28:55.067
Did you see that was Hugh Morrison?
Jane.

473
00:28:56.535 --> 00:28:57.815
You seem like you're miles away.

474
00:29:00.106 --> 00:29:01.340
No. I just had a weird day.

475
00:29:02.674 --> 00:29:04.086
What's the matter? Are you okay?

476
00:29:04.110 --> 00:29:07.689
Yeah. Yeah. I ran
into someone today.

477
00:29:07.713 --> 00:29:10.049
Really? Who? Found you. Yes.

478
00:29:14.386 --> 00:29:16.198
You must be Jane's friend.

479
00:29:16.222 --> 00:29:17.599
Hi.

480
00:29:17.623 --> 00:29:22.871
Hugh. this is Michael. my
friend from childhood.

481
00:29:22.895 --> 00:29:25.607
And we ran into each other today.
That's fantastic.

482
00:29:25.631 --> 00:29:27.366
Hi. Good to see you. Hey.

483
00:29:28.100 --> 00:29:29.635
Can I sit down?

484
00:29:32.204 --> 00:29:34.974
Yeah. of course. Of course. please.
Yeah. please do.

485
00:29:36.442 --> 00:29:39.487
Michael. this is
Hugh. my fiance.

486
00:29:39.511 --> 00:29:41.689
So. honey. we should
probably look at the menu.

487
00:29:41.713 --> 00:29:43.473
because. you know. if
the waitress comes over

488
00:29:43.497 --> 00:29:45.708
and I don't know what I want.
that'll send her away.

489
00:29:45.732 --> 00:29:49.155
then it takes 20 minutes for her to come
back. and that's a long time. so...

490
00:29:51.858 --> 00:29:55.103
So what do you do?

491
00:29:55.127 --> 00:29:58.273
I'm a friend for children
who need a little support.

492
00:29:58.297 --> 00:30:00.008
A teacher. He's a teacher.

493
00:30:00.032 --> 00:30:02.077
A teacher. My mother
was a teacher.

494
00:30:02.101 --> 00:30:04.813
That's such a noble profession.

495
00:30:04.837 --> 00:30:08.540
She used to say. "Teaching
feeds the soul of a child."

496
00:30:10.843 --> 00:30:13.889
I had a teacher once who inspired me to
read the works of Tolstoy and Camus...

497
00:30:13.913 --> 00:30:17.549
Jane. Jane used to read the
works of Nancy Drew mysteries.

498
00:30:23.489 --> 00:30:27.002
Michael. Michael. I don't
remember you mentioning...

499
00:30:27.026 --> 00:30:28.636
What is your last name?

500
00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:29.896
Friend.

501
00:30:30.596 --> 00:30:31.697
Michael Friend.

502
00:30:32.331 --> 00:30:34.076
Michael Friend.

503
00:30:34.100 --> 00:30:37.445
You know. we used to
call him the Friendster.

504
00:30:37.469 --> 00:30:40.015
Michael Friend is a
good name for me.

505
00:30:40.039 --> 00:30:42.985
It's a great name. Yeah.

506
00:30:43.009 --> 00:30:46.121
Finally. We're both gonna
have the chicken marsala

507
00:30:46.145 --> 00:30:48.556
with the vegetables
instead of the potatoes.

508
00:30:48.580 --> 00:30:50.220
Can you ask them to
hurry it. too. please?

509
00:30:50.244 --> 00:30:52.460
Doesn't that come
with mushrooms?

510
00:30:52.484 --> 00:30:55.898
I mean. just checking. because I know
you... Mushrooms make you throw up.

511
00:30:55.922 --> 00:30:58.524
Yeah. I'm allergic. You are?

512
00:30:59.691 --> 00:31:02.270
Yeah. I didn't know that.

513
00:31:02.294 --> 00:31:04.039
It's okay. I'll just
eat around them.

514
00:31:04.063 --> 00:31:08.043
Well. why don't you get something
different. that won't make you sick?

515
00:31:08.067 --> 00:31:12.771
Okay. yeah. I will have
the spaghetti bolognese.

516
00:31:14.773 --> 00:31:18.220
That sounds great. I'll also do that.
Hugh. you wanna change your order. too?

517
00:31:18.244 --> 00:31:21.323
No. Pasta this late at night?
No. thank you.

518
00:31:21.347 --> 00:31:24.893
Come on. It gives you energy for later
when you guys wrestle around in bed.

519
00:31:24.917 --> 00:31:27.795
She's a tough cookie. am
I right or am I right?

520
00:31:27.819 --> 00:31:28.988
Right.

521
00:31:33.392 --> 00:31:37.572
So. Hugh. you're marrying Jane.

522
00:31:37.596 --> 00:31:41.733
Wow. you are so lucky. Tell
me what you love about her.

523
00:31:47.073 --> 00:31:48.374
I love...

524
00:31:49.475 --> 00:31:51.353
She's so organized.

525
00:31:51.377 --> 00:31:54.356
You know. she has my whole life on track.
She has me on a schedule.

526
00:31:54.380 --> 00:31:55.757
It really works. too.

527
00:31:55.781 --> 00:31:58.860
I mean. she's the reason I
got my book done in time.

528
00:31:58.884 --> 00:32:02.321
Well. those are things you can accomplish
with a datebook and a clock. though.

529
00:32:03.822 --> 00:32:05.824
What do you love about her?

530
00:32:09.228 --> 00:32:11.197
Michael. I'm not sure I
understand your question.

531
00:32:13.032 --> 00:32:15.867
Well. you know. I mean.
she's super funny.

532
00:32:16.802 --> 00:32:18.280
Isn't she?

533
00:32:18.304 --> 00:32:21.116
Come on. She's
incredibly creative.

534
00:32:21.140 --> 00:32:25.587
I personally love how when she runs and her
ponytail just swings from side to side.

535
00:32:25.611 --> 00:32:28.490
It's great.

536
00:32:28.514 --> 00:32:30.993
And you got to love how
she sings in her sleep.

537
00:32:31.017 --> 00:32:33.257
You slept together? Well. she
doesn't like to sleep alone.

538
00:32:33.281 --> 00:32:36.084
We napped together in
kindergarten on a mat.

539
00:32:38.790 --> 00:32:40.635
Michael... Totally innocent.

540
00:32:40.659 --> 00:32:42.670
So. are you married?

541
00:32:42.694 --> 00:32:46.108
No. No. You know. I'm never
in one place very long.

542
00:32:46.132 --> 00:32:48.460
My work kind of takes
me all over the world.

543
00:32:48.472 --> 00:32:50.812
so I'm never sure where
I'm gonna be sent.

544
00:32:50.836 --> 00:32:54.116
Dr. Sellars. would you
mind signing our menu?

545
00:32:54.140 --> 00:32:55.374
Sure.

546
00:32:56.475 --> 00:32:57.919
Wait. you're a doctor?

547
00:32:57.943 --> 00:32:59.487
No. he's an actor.

548
00:32:59.511 --> 00:33:01.323
An actor?

549
00:33:01.347 --> 00:33:04.516
Well. we must've seen him in one of the
million movies we watched together?

550
00:33:31.377 --> 00:33:35.323
Well. Michael. good to meet you.
Hope to see you again sometime.

551
00:33:35.347 --> 00:33:39.094
You. too. Thank you for paying for
dinner. by the way. I don't have money.

552
00:33:39.118 --> 00:33:41.196
I know. Teachers are
so underappreciated.

553
00:33:41.220 --> 00:33:43.965
I mean. when you compare their
salaries to what actors make. it's...

554
00:33:43.989 --> 00:33:45.400
I've never needed
it until today.

555
00:33:45.424 --> 00:33:47.635
Yeah. right. it's a
whole different world.

556
00:33:47.659 --> 00:33:50.172
No. the world is still the same.
I'm the one who's changed.

557
00:33:50.196 --> 00:33:51.330
Yeah.

558
00:33:54.633 --> 00:33:56.102
Got you last.

559
00:33:57.803 --> 00:33:59.114
Yeah. okay. Take care.

560
00:33:59.138 --> 00:34:00.906
All right. you. too.

561
00:34:02.608 --> 00:34:04.110
See you later.

562
00:34:22.294 --> 00:34:24.029
He's a handsome guy.

563
00:34:26.465 --> 00:34:27.799
Friendly.

564
00:34:28.600 --> 00:34:30.545
A little odd.

565
00:34:30.569 --> 00:34:34.616
Must've been great to reconnect
with him after all these years.

566
00:34:34.640 --> 00:34:38.110
You gonna see him again?
No. I don't think so. No.

567
00:34:42.013 --> 00:34:43.882
Knows a lot about you.

568
00:34:45.484 --> 00:34:46.585
Yeah.

569
00:34:48.120 --> 00:34:50.021
I guess he always did.

570
00:35:02.768 --> 00:35:03.878
Thank you.

571
00:35:03.902 --> 00:35:06.238
I got it. Happy holidays to you.

572
00:35:08.307 --> 00:35:12.820
It's a great building. Nice to
be so close to the park. huh?

573
00:35:12.844 --> 00:35:14.756
Michael? You're here?

574
00:35:14.780 --> 00:35:15.981
I know.

575
00:35:23.622 --> 00:35:26.768
Okay. look. Listen. if you wanna get in
touch with me. here's my business card.

576
00:35:26.792 --> 00:35:28.203
You can call me. okay?

577
00:35:28.227 --> 00:35:30.338
Good night. Great.

578
00:35:30.362 --> 00:35:32.540
Hugh doesn't live with you?

579
00:35:32.564 --> 00:35:34.509
No. Hugh needs his rest
when he's doing a play.

580
00:35:34.533 --> 00:35:36.878
and I wake up early.
so that wakes him up.

581
00:35:36.902 --> 00:35:40.215
And after we get married. I'm
gonna move into his place.

582
00:35:40.239 --> 00:35:42.784
I don't know why I'm telling you this.
Good night.

583
00:35:42.808 --> 00:35:45.611
Good night. Sweet dreams.
You. too.

584
00:35:52.150 --> 00:35:54.162
Are you sleeping out here?

585
00:35:54.186 --> 00:35:56.130
Yeah. I'll be fine.

586
00:35:56.154 --> 00:35:58.023
It'll be like when
we went camping.

587
00:35:59.024 --> 00:36:00.502
We never went camping.

588
00:36:00.526 --> 00:36:03.238
Yes. we did. We made a tent
out of sheets on the balcony

589
00:36:03.262 --> 00:36:05.431
and roasted marshmallows
in your EasyBake Oven.

590
00:36:06.064 --> 00:36:07.766
Yeah. that was fun.

591
00:36:10.502 --> 00:36:13.348
I liked Hugh. He's wonderful.

592
00:36:13.372 --> 00:36:17.409
I know. I can see why you love him.
He's an actor with really white teeth.

593
00:36:19.044 --> 00:36:21.680
That's not why I love him.
Good night.

594
00:36:22.714 --> 00:36:24.082
Good night.

595
00:36:37.863 --> 00:36:40.342
Okay. you can stay one night.

596
00:36:40.366 --> 00:36:45.046
He always does this. the super. He
leaves me a note. He has a key.

597
00:36:45.070 --> 00:36:47.181
He could just let himself
in and fix the shower.

598
00:36:47.205 --> 00:36:49.584
but instead he leaves me a note.

599
00:36:49.608 --> 00:36:53.087
But I guess I have bigger
problems than a broken shower.

600
00:36:53.111 --> 00:36:56.291
The whole place could use
a paint job. you know?

601
00:36:56.315 --> 00:37:00.194
Sorry about the mess. Hugh keeps
promising to help me. but...

602
00:37:00.218 --> 00:37:04.299
You know what? I guess it
doesn't really matter.

603
00:37:04.323 --> 00:37:07.435
Not gonna be here much longer.

604
00:37:07.459 --> 00:37:11.096
I couldn't just let you sleep
outside. right? It's too cold.

605
00:37:12.531 --> 00:37:14.141
Okay.

606
00:37:14.165 --> 00:37:16.468
You can just sleep on the couch.

607
00:37:17.569 --> 00:37:19.080
Okay.

608
00:37:19.104 --> 00:37:21.015
Michael. why are you here?

609
00:37:21.039 --> 00:37:24.652
The only thing I can figure out is
that I must be here to help you.

610
00:37:24.676 --> 00:37:25.987
So what's wrong. Jane?

611
00:37:26.011 --> 00:37:30.458
Nothing. I'm fine.
I don't need help.

612
00:37:30.482 --> 00:37:33.295
Great. then I was right.
About what?

613
00:37:33.319 --> 00:37:37.865
I always knew you would grow up and
become an amazing. beautiful woman.

614
00:37:37.889 --> 00:37:39.489
I'm just glad I get
to be here to see it.

615
00:37:42.060 --> 00:37:45.673
That's... So. thank you

616
00:37:45.697 --> 00:37:51.513
for coming all the way back
here from magic land. You know?

617
00:37:51.537 --> 00:37:54.816
Sleep well. See you
in the morning.

618
00:37:54.840 --> 00:37:56.074
Thanks.

619
00:38:06.818 --> 00:38:08.219
Jane? Yeah?

620
00:38:08.987 --> 00:38:10.021
Proud of you.

621
00:38:25.771 --> 00:38:27.138
No! No!

622
00:38:31.977 --> 00:38:33.588
What are you doing in here?

623
00:38:33.612 --> 00:38:35.492
I thought you might still
be afraid of the dark.

624
00:38:37.716 --> 00:38:39.494
Go back into the other room.

625
00:38:39.518 --> 00:38:40.652
Okay.

626
00:38:46.992 --> 00:38:49.337
This isn't happening.

627
00:38:49.361 --> 00:38:51.539
You've had a brain aneurysm.

628
00:38:51.563 --> 00:38:55.510
You're in a coma in the hospital. but
your mind is living this nightmare

629
00:38:55.534 --> 00:38:58.370
and just waiting for
you to wake up.

630
00:39:09.581 --> 00:39:11.926
Jane. Hi. dear.

631
00:39:11.950 --> 00:39:14.028
There's my girl.

632
00:39:14.052 --> 00:39:17.665
Did you know Mr. Danderford played the
clarinet at the Blue Note in the late '50s

633
00:39:17.689 --> 00:39:20.267
and Mrs. Greenberg was
a waitress there?

634
00:39:20.291 --> 00:39:22.691
And they've lived down the hall
from each other all this time.

635
00:39:22.715 --> 00:39:24.326
and they never put
that together.

636
00:39:24.350 --> 00:39:25.640
It's amazing.

637
00:39:25.664 --> 00:39:27.809
So. I see you guys have all met.

638
00:39:27.833 --> 00:39:31.979
Well. finish your coffee.
I've got to go to work. okay?

639
00:39:32.003 --> 00:39:34.677
Here's a key. So when
you're finished. just

640
00:39:34.689 --> 00:39:37.375
lock up and put the key
under the mat. Bye.

641
00:39:45.016 --> 00:39:47.228
Mom. do you remember
when I was a little girl

642
00:39:47.252 --> 00:39:49.797
and I had an imaginary
friend named Michael?

643
00:39:49.821 --> 00:39:51.899
Yeah. do I ever.

644
00:39:51.923 --> 00:39:54.702
I even sent you to Dr.
Nussbaum for therapy.

645
00:39:54.726 --> 00:39:57.439
and he told me that I should let
you keep your little friend

646
00:39:57.463 --> 00:39:59.140
because he made you happy.

647
00:39:59.164 --> 00:40:03.101
and he was sure that one day he
would leave. and thank God he did.

648
00:40:05.871 --> 00:40:06.972
Why?

649
00:40:08.139 --> 00:40:11.085
I just ran into someone
that reminds me of him.

650
00:40:11.109 --> 00:40:13.287
Oh. my God. you're
having an affair.

651
00:40:13.311 --> 00:40:17.324
Does Hugh know? No. I am not
having an affair. Mother.

652
00:40:17.348 --> 00:40:20.828
I just... You know. I ran in...

653
00:40:20.852 --> 00:40:22.363
You know what it is.

654
00:40:22.387 --> 00:40:24.666
It doesn't matter. It's wedding jitters.
Buyer's remorse.

655
00:40:24.690 --> 00:40:26.568
You two are perfect together.
I know.

656
00:40:26.592 --> 00:40:29.471
Well. as perfect as it
can get in this world.

657
00:40:29.495 --> 00:40:31.272
God. that's so cynical.

658
00:40:31.296 --> 00:40:33.140
No. it isn't.

659
00:40:33.164 --> 00:40:36.410
Jane. I just don't
want you to miss out.

660
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:41.415
I waited a long time for Mr. Right
and what I got was your father.

661
00:40:41.439 --> 00:40:43.041
a charming. cheating
bastard who left us.

662
00:40:45.711 --> 00:40:49.090
Hugh is a wonderful catch
and he adores you.

663
00:40:49.114 --> 00:40:51.125
And I love him.

664
00:40:51.149 --> 00:40:52.818
Of course you do.

665
00:41:11.436 --> 00:41:13.715
Martha Stewart's daughter was
my assignment for a year

666
00:41:13.739 --> 00:41:17.108
when her mom's company went
public and she got really busy.

667
00:41:19.745 --> 00:41:20.812
What do you think?

668
00:41:23.048 --> 00:41:25.326
It's amazing.

669
00:41:25.350 --> 00:41:27.753
I can't believe you
did all of this.

670
00:41:28.687 --> 00:41:30.197
Come here.

671
00:41:30.221 --> 00:41:32.524
Your hands are freezing.

672
00:41:37.328 --> 00:41:39.531
And you even put
together my TV stand.

673
00:41:40.632 --> 00:41:42.668
And this was all I needed.

674
00:41:49.407 --> 00:41:51.977
No one's ever done anything
like this for me before.

675
00:41:54.379 --> 00:41:55.581
Why not?

676
00:41:57.048 --> 00:41:59.293
I don't know.

677
00:41:59.317 --> 00:42:02.487
People have their own lives.
They get busy.

678
00:42:09.227 --> 00:42:10.295
What is that smell?

679
00:42:11.296 --> 00:42:13.264
I made you mac and cheese.

680
00:42:14.065 --> 00:42:15.934
I love mac and cheese.

681
00:42:26.712 --> 00:42:29.991
The Adventures of
Michael and Jane.

682
00:42:30.015 --> 00:42:33.384
Wow. I haven't looked
at this in forever.

683
00:42:35.654 --> 00:42:36.688
I know.

684
00:42:37.823 --> 00:42:40.134
I have something to show you.
What?

685
00:42:40.158 --> 00:42:43.061
Go in the bathroom. turn on the
shower. and take off your clothes.

686
00:42:47.899 --> 00:42:48.900
What?

687
00:42:50.101 --> 00:42:52.537
No! I can't do that.

688
00:42:55.040 --> 00:42:57.475
"Take off your clothes."
I fixed your shower!

689
00:42:59.144 --> 00:43:02.380
I was a friend to a kid
whose father was a plumber.

690
00:43:04.315 --> 00:43:06.351
I thought you wanted to...

691
00:43:08.219 --> 00:43:10.965
I wasn't always Don Juan.

692
00:43:10.989 --> 00:43:15.870
I wasn't always an actor. and Hamlet
wasn't always my favorite role.

693
00:43:15.894 --> 00:43:19.731
I was first John Sidney
Blyth Barrymore.

694
00:43:20.966 --> 00:43:23.735
a young boy with big dreams.

695
00:43:25.971 --> 00:43:27.581
although not always
focused on the stage.

696
00:43:27.605 --> 00:43:29.174
Vivian. hi.

697
00:43:30.341 --> 00:43:32.053
I'm sorry that I misjudged you.

698
00:43:32.077 --> 00:43:34.321
Jane says you've really
grown into a better mother.

699
00:43:34.345 --> 00:43:36.490
Thank you. Yeah.

700
00:43:36.514 --> 00:43:38.225
Who are you?

701
00:43:38.249 --> 00:43:42.463
Michael. Well. you used to call
me the delusion. remember?

702
00:43:42.487 --> 00:43:44.607
You were probably just trying
to protect Jane from love

703
00:43:44.631 --> 00:43:46.067
because you'd been so hurt.

704
00:43:46.091 --> 00:43:48.736
You weren't being mean. You
were simply misguided.

705
00:43:48.760 --> 00:43:51.505
It's okay. I forgive you.

706
00:43:51.529 --> 00:43:55.000
I live between polite
society and the bordello.

707
00:43:56.735 --> 00:44:00.782
It wasn't until 1903 that I
made my debut as a thespian.

708
00:44:00.806 --> 00:44:02.383
And by 1905.

709
00:44:02.407 --> 00:44:05.419
I was firmly implanted
in the London stage.

710
00:44:05.443 --> 00:44:09.757
The theater was my salvation when
television became redundant. you know.

711
00:44:09.781 --> 00:44:13.527
But film is the dream. It
keeps me reaching inside.

712
00:44:13.551 --> 00:44:15.763
You know what I mean? Excuse me.

713
00:44:15.787 --> 00:44:17.498
Hi. Hi.

714
00:44:17.522 --> 00:44:21.368
This is a surprise. Michael's here.
Yeah.

715
00:44:21.392 --> 00:44:24.105
I'm not sure I like you spending
so much time with the other guy.

716
00:44:24.129 --> 00:44:26.507
Oh. stop. He's just
an old friend.

717
00:44:26.531 --> 00:44:29.276
You are the love of my life.

718
00:44:29.300 --> 00:44:30.635
Who? You.

719
00:44:34.005 --> 00:44:35.365
Sorry. I just get
a little jealous.

720
00:44:36.341 --> 00:44:37.584
You were wonderful. by the way.

721
00:44:37.608 --> 00:44:40.021
Thanks. man. You're
an amazing actor.

722
00:44:40.045 --> 00:44:42.881
Thank you. man. I really
believed you were a doctor.

723
00:44:44.950 --> 00:44:48.062
He actually wasn't a doctor.
He wasn't playing a doctor.

724
00:44:48.086 --> 00:44:50.264
Well. you were
stupendous tonight.

725
00:44:50.288 --> 00:44:52.133
Thank you. Vivian.

726
00:44:52.157 --> 00:44:54.597
You know you would've gotten a
standing ovation if the audience

727
00:44:54.621 --> 00:44:57.004
wasn't riveted to their
seats by your performance.

728
00:44:57.028 --> 00:44:59.273
You look great. Thank you.

729
00:44:59.297 --> 00:45:01.767
Yeah. My daughter's
a lucky woman.

730
00:45:03.034 --> 00:45:05.312
Aren't you. honey? Yes. I am.

731
00:45:05.336 --> 00:45:07.806
Come on. someone
wants to meet you.

732
00:45:10.075 --> 00:45:12.419
Hugh is really talented. I know.

733
00:45:12.443 --> 00:45:15.622
Your mother's the same
as she always was.

734
00:45:15.646 --> 00:45:16.714
I know.

735
00:45:24.422 --> 00:45:26.267
Morning.

736
00:45:26.291 --> 00:45:28.426
Hi. Going to work?

737
00:45:30.161 --> 00:45:32.539
No. the theater's
dark on Mondays.

738
00:45:32.563 --> 00:45:35.200
Great. What do you
wanna do today?

739
00:45:37.535 --> 00:45:39.981
Want to go to the museum?

740
00:45:40.005 --> 00:45:43.842
Or. you know. maybe we
could just stay home?

741
00:45:48.914 --> 00:45:52.750
I have a very full day.

742
00:45:54.052 --> 00:45:56.621
I have a wedding to plan.

743
00:46:05.363 --> 00:46:06.664
I'm just...

744
00:46:07.632 --> 00:46:09.901
I'm just gonna get dressed now.

745
00:46:11.536 --> 00:46:12.703
Right.

746
00:46:16.975 --> 00:46:18.743
Do you want me to...

747
00:46:19.710 --> 00:46:21.923
I'll just...

748
00:46:21.947 --> 00:46:26.127
So. it's been three months and you've
narrowed it down to these seven.

749
00:46:26.151 --> 00:46:29.030
With Christmas orders piling up. I
really need you to make a decision

750
00:46:29.054 --> 00:46:31.232
on what direction you wanna go.
I know. I know.

751
00:46:31.256 --> 00:46:33.400
I just don't think
that I can choose yet.

752
00:46:33.424 --> 00:46:37.138
And they're all beautiful. It's
just that Hugh is very particular.

753
00:46:37.162 --> 00:46:38.663
and everything has
to be perfect.

754
00:46:40.498 --> 00:46:42.409
You want that one.

755
00:46:42.433 --> 00:46:45.212
This one? Yeah.

756
00:46:45.236 --> 00:46:47.248
Yeah. pink and green are
your favorite colors.

757
00:46:47.272 --> 00:46:50.184
and roses remind you
of your Grandma Rose.

758
00:46:50.208 --> 00:46:53.754
Yeah. you're right.
I'll take this one.

759
00:46:53.778 --> 00:46:55.890
Wonderful.

760
00:46:55.914 --> 00:46:59.093
You should bring your fiance with
you on all your appointments.

761
00:46:59.117 --> 00:47:00.862
He's not my fiance.

762
00:47:00.886 --> 00:47:02.854
He's just a good friend.

763
00:47:06.457 --> 00:47:09.560
You must like boys. Am I right?

764
00:47:10.761 --> 00:47:13.464
I like girls and boys. Yeah.

765
00:47:19.204 --> 00:47:22.783
Wow. Chocolate is... No. There
are no words for chocolate.

766
00:47:22.807 --> 00:47:25.386
New words will have to be
invented for this experience.

767
00:47:25.410 --> 00:47:29.090
And the strawberry. Strawberry
tastes like summer afternoons

768
00:47:29.114 --> 00:47:31.792
when you've been outside
playing and swimming all day.

769
00:47:31.816 --> 00:47:34.628
and then you come inside. and
you're hungry and thirsty.

770
00:47:34.652 --> 00:47:36.021
Strawberry.

771
00:47:50.969 --> 00:47:52.803
It's clouds of awesome.

772
00:47:53.438 --> 00:47:55.040
This is the one!

773
00:47:57.542 --> 00:48:00.445
Let's go to the dress shop next. I've
narrowed it down to six dresses.

774
00:48:01.246 --> 00:48:03.891
I already know the one.

775
00:48:03.915 --> 00:48:06.493
I still don't know
why we're here.

776
00:48:06.517 --> 00:48:08.795
Do you remember the
first play we went to?

777
00:48:08.819 --> 00:48:13.258
Of course. It was my favorite.
One Special Night.

778
00:48:18.596 --> 00:48:20.574
That's my dress.

779
00:48:20.598 --> 00:48:23.878
You said that the first night you saw it.
when the actor stepped out on stage in it.

780
00:48:28.439 --> 00:48:29.674
Come on.

781
00:48:44.322 --> 00:48:45.556
Wow.

782
00:48:46.224 --> 00:48:47.959
You look beautiful.

783
00:48:48.393 --> 00:48:49.560
I do?

784
00:48:52.863 --> 00:48:54.099
Thanks.

785
00:49:10.681 --> 00:49:11.949
What just happened?

786
00:49:13.418 --> 00:49:16.763
We kissed. No. we didn't.

787
00:49:16.787 --> 00:49:18.865
That just didn't happen.
That was wonderful.

788
00:49:18.889 --> 00:49:20.729
How could it be wonderful
if it never happened?

789
00:49:20.753 --> 00:49:22.603
That was our first kiss.
It was our last kiss.

790
00:49:22.627 --> 00:49:24.305
They say you never
forget your first kiss.

791
00:49:24.329 --> 00:49:25.930
Forget it. okay?

792
00:49:28.399 --> 00:49:29.467
Oh. my God.

793
00:49:32.337 --> 00:49:37.051
It did happen. but it was a horrible
mistake. and it can never happen again.

794
00:49:37.075 --> 00:49:38.155
It was an accident. Exactly.

795
00:49:38.179 --> 00:49:40.321
I just tripped and
fell on your lips.

796
00:49:40.345 --> 00:49:43.324
Michael. I'm serious right now.
That can never happen again.

797
00:49:43.348 --> 00:49:45.159
Yeah. we'll avoid
it at all cost.

798
00:49:45.183 --> 00:49:50.097
I'm about to marry Hugh Morrison. okay?
A man that I love very. very much.

799
00:49:50.121 --> 00:49:51.632
I believe you.

800
00:49:51.656 --> 00:49:55.669
No. I'm not trying to convince
you. you know? It's a fact.

801
00:49:55.693 --> 00:49:58.539
It's just I was very excited
because we found the dress.

802
00:49:58.563 --> 00:50:03.644
and so. you know. stuff happened.
and it didn't mean anything at all.

803
00:50:03.668 --> 00:50:05.746
It was just a kiss
between old friends.

804
00:50:05.770 --> 00:50:07.081
Right. Right.

805
00:50:07.105 --> 00:50:09.983
So we're clear. Just friends.
Best friends.

806
00:50:10.007 --> 00:50:12.610
Okay. You need to
stop following me.

807
00:50:27.892 --> 00:50:30.395
Hey. Paul. How's it going?
Good to see you.

808
00:50:32.697 --> 00:50:34.065
Who's this?

809
00:50:37.034 --> 00:50:38.703
Hi. Nathan. I'm Michael. Hi.

810
00:50:39.704 --> 00:50:42.383
Wait. you can see Paul?

811
00:50:42.407 --> 00:50:44.285
Sure. Yes!

812
00:50:44.309 --> 00:50:45.719
I knew he was real.

813
00:50:45.743 --> 00:50:48.021
Wait. Who are you talking to?
Who is Paul?

814
00:50:48.045 --> 00:50:49.490
He's an imaginary.

815
00:50:49.514 --> 00:50:51.558
Right.

816
00:50:51.582 --> 00:50:54.595
For a second there. I thought you
were talking to an empty chair. so...

817
00:50:54.619 --> 00:50:55.686
No.

818
00:50:59.990 --> 00:51:02.803
Hi. You can't keep
showing up like this.

819
00:51:02.827 --> 00:51:04.371
I do have patients.

820
00:51:04.395 --> 00:51:06.673
Nathan's fine. He's sitting out there
with an invisible boy named Paul

821
00:51:06.697 --> 00:51:08.242
and my imaginary
friend. Michael.

822
00:51:08.266 --> 00:51:09.443
Okay. now you're scaring me.

823
00:51:09.467 --> 00:51:10.968
Ask me what I did today.

824
00:51:12.637 --> 00:51:15.149
I chose my cake. I
chose my flowers.

825
00:51:15.173 --> 00:51:18.018
and my wedding dress all
within the last three hours.

826
00:51:18.042 --> 00:51:20.521
Why? Because I had
Michael with me.

827
00:51:20.545 --> 00:51:23.090
Great. It's crazy. isn't it?

828
00:51:23.114 --> 00:51:24.758
Well. I don't know if
it's crazy or not.

829
00:51:24.782 --> 00:51:28.429
but your eyes do light up every
time you talk about Michael.

830
00:51:28.453 --> 00:51:29.663
No. they don't. Yeah. they do.

831
00:51:29.687 --> 00:51:32.056
You have this twinkle... No.
Okay. I kissed him.

832
00:51:34.792 --> 00:51:37.904
I kissed him. yeah. So
he found the dress.

833
00:51:37.928 --> 00:51:41.932
and I was really happy. and he
thought I looked beautiful. and...

834
00:51:44.402 --> 00:51:45.646
And?

835
00:51:45.670 --> 00:51:48.373
And we kissed. and
now it's over.

836
00:51:50.775 --> 00:51:53.387
So you're still in
human limbo. I see.

837
00:51:53.411 --> 00:51:56.323
It's so weird. Everyone's
talking about it.

838
00:51:56.347 --> 00:51:59.560
Every imaginary should
do it at least once.

839
00:51:59.584 --> 00:52:01.828
Feelings are so much
bigger than we thought.

840
00:52:01.852 --> 00:52:05.266
Your kid gets picked last for baseball.
and we tell him it's nothing.

841
00:52:05.290 --> 00:52:07.258
It's not nothing. It hurts.

842
00:52:18.569 --> 00:52:21.982
That cute guy out there
is your Michael?

843
00:52:22.006 --> 00:52:28.121
No. he is not my Michael. he's
just Michael. a good friend.

844
00:52:28.145 --> 00:52:33.594
He's living with you. He's one door
away. sleeping naked on a white sheet.

845
00:52:33.618 --> 00:52:35.962
How do you stand it? How do
you know he sleeps naked?

846
00:52:35.986 --> 00:52:38.265
That's how I picture him.

847
00:52:38.289 --> 00:52:42.135
Okay. stop. Just stop.

848
00:52:42.159 --> 00:52:48.209
I love Hugh. Hugh is a wonderful man. and
I am the luckiest girl in the world.

849
00:52:48.233 --> 00:52:51.278
All I know is if I had a man
who looked at me like that.

850
00:52:51.302 --> 00:52:53.447
I would never get out of bed.

851
00:52:53.471 --> 00:52:54.948
Hugh looks at me like that.

852
00:52:54.972 --> 00:52:56.407
Hugh looks at himself like that.

853
00:53:02.480 --> 00:53:05.158
That was fun. So what's next?

854
00:53:05.182 --> 00:53:09.230
Nothing. We got everything. The
cake. the flowers. the dress.

855
00:53:09.254 --> 00:53:11.121
Nice. Let's celebrate.

856
00:53:13.291 --> 00:53:16.361
Martini. olives. Crazy week.

857
00:53:16.861 --> 00:53:18.104
For you?

858
00:53:18.128 --> 00:53:21.198
Martini. olives. Crazy week.

859
00:53:23.268 --> 00:53:25.846
That's great music.

860
00:53:25.870 --> 00:53:29.006
Jane and I love to dance.
No. we don't.

861
00:53:30.040 --> 00:53:31.685
Are you kidding me?

862
00:53:31.709 --> 00:53:35.021
You used to dance in front
of the mirror all the time.

863
00:53:35.045 --> 00:53:40.093
Like a Virgin. The
song Like a Virgin.

864
00:53:40.117 --> 00:53:42.296
(SONG U CAN'T TOUCH THIS BEGINS)

865
00:53:42.320 --> 00:53:47.525
No way. Are you kidding?
What time is it?

866
00:53:48.593 --> 00:53:49.703
I don't know.

867
00:53:49.727 --> 00:53:50.995
Jane.

868
00:53:52.630 --> 00:53:54.299
Hammer time. It's Hammer time!

869
00:54:01.372 --> 00:54:03.040
He's not from around here.

870
00:54:15.152 --> 00:54:16.432
Can't believe this is happening.

871
00:54:38.809 --> 00:54:41.522
That was amazing. Awesome.

872
00:54:41.546 --> 00:54:42.547
(APPLAUSE)

873
00:56:33.624 --> 00:56:36.670
Look at them. What
a sweet couple.

874
00:56:36.694 --> 00:56:39.464
Probably been together for 50 years.
Yeah.

875
00:56:40.197 --> 00:56:42.676
It looks that way.

876
00:56:42.700 --> 00:56:46.904
but the truth is. they just met
an hour ago in yoga class.

877
00:56:47.672 --> 00:56:50.784
Really? Yeah.

878
00:56:50.808 --> 00:56:53.620
Yeah. I mean. they've been
seeing each other for years.

879
00:56:53.644 --> 00:56:57.624
But. you know. a little yoga class
here. a meditation group there.

880
00:56:57.648 --> 00:56:59.984
This is the first time they
ever talked to each other.

881
00:57:01.118 --> 00:57:02.429
Why today?

882
00:57:02.453 --> 00:57:06.223
Well. because today
is Evelyn's birthday.

883
00:57:08.058 --> 00:57:12.930
And she is planning on spending the
entire weekend in a nudist colony.

884
00:57:14.732 --> 00:57:18.645
Name? Of the nudist colony?
The Bare Inn.

885
00:57:18.669 --> 00:57:20.180
Wow. Yeah.

886
00:57:20.204 --> 00:57:23.216
Do you think he'll go with her?
I do. actually. I do.

887
00:57:23.240 --> 00:57:25.919
Because it's also
Phil's birthday.

888
00:57:25.943 --> 00:57:30.447
Yeah. And they will quickly realize that
the best way to spend their birthdays

889
00:57:31.348 --> 00:57:33.450
is in their birthday suits.

890
00:57:37.387 --> 00:57:38.422
Excellent.

891
00:57:42.259 --> 00:57:44.471
So Hugh's gonna pick me
up for the book signing.

892
00:57:44.495 --> 00:57:47.107
And I don't know if
you're gonna go out.

893
00:57:47.131 --> 00:57:49.033
So are you?

894
00:57:50.234 --> 00:57:51.969
Am I what? Gonna go out?

895
00:57:52.570 --> 00:57:55.215
I don't think so.

896
00:57:55.239 --> 00:57:56.999
I don't know. I wasn't
really planning on it.

897
00:57:57.808 --> 00:58:00.420
Don't know a lot of
people here. so...

898
00:58:00.444 --> 00:58:01.445
Right.

899
00:58:02.913 --> 00:58:05.182
You'll be okay? Yeah. sure.

900
00:58:06.784 --> 00:58:07.852
Hey.

901
00:58:12.189 --> 00:58:14.258
I do not want to
have a pillow fight.

902
00:58:18.328 --> 00:58:20.264
You're kidding me.

903
00:58:25.202 --> 00:58:27.037
I have always wanted
a pillow fight!

904
00:58:34.278 --> 00:58:37.423
Hi. honey. What's going on?

905
00:58:37.447 --> 00:58:40.126
Nothing. I've been
calling you all day.

906
00:58:40.150 --> 00:58:43.754
Yeah. we went out. We were
planning our wedding.

907
00:58:46.456 --> 00:58:50.761
Our wedding. not our wedding.

908
00:58:51.428 --> 00:58:52.563
Right.

909
00:58:54.331 --> 00:58:55.976
I don't understand
why he's still here.

910
00:58:56.000 --> 00:58:58.178
He's got nowhere else to go.

911
00:58:58.202 --> 00:59:00.781
Hugh. he's just a friend. You
have no reason to be jealous.

912
00:59:00.805 --> 00:59:02.749
Jealous? No. I'm not jealous.

913
00:59:02.773 --> 00:59:05.318
Excuse me if I don't want my
wife living with another man!

914
00:59:05.342 --> 00:59:08.454
I'm not your wife yet. And keep
your voice down. He can hear you.

915
00:59:08.478 --> 00:59:10.190
He's using you.

916
00:59:10.214 --> 00:59:11.858
He is not using me.

917
00:59:11.882 --> 00:59:15.095
Really? Why did he show up now?

918
00:59:15.119 --> 00:59:19.199
After all these years. right when
you're about to marry a famous actor?

919
00:59:19.223 --> 00:59:20.858
What does he want?

920
00:59:22.660 --> 00:59:24.404
You're so naive.

921
00:59:24.428 --> 00:59:27.140
You know. people. they take
advantage of you all the time.

922
00:59:27.164 --> 00:59:30.210
like those old people that guilt you
into running their errands for them.

923
00:59:30.234 --> 00:59:33.079
They're my neighbors.

924
00:59:33.103 --> 00:59:36.149
You care about this guy so much that
you're gonna let him come in between us?

925
00:59:36.173 --> 00:59:38.652
No. No. of course not.

926
00:59:38.676 --> 00:59:40.286
He's just got no
place else to stay.

927
00:59:40.310 --> 00:59:43.423
I don't care! He's
got no job. no life.

928
00:59:43.447 --> 00:59:47.017
I just feel sorry for him. I
don't care about him at all.

929
00:59:51.021 --> 00:59:53.257
Ten minutes. then I'm gone.

930
01:00:09.006 --> 01:00:10.166
I didn't mean it in that way.

931
01:00:12.542 --> 01:00:13.610
But?

932
01:00:14.712 --> 01:00:17.257
But Hugh's my future.

933
01:00:17.281 --> 01:00:18.749
He's going to be my husband.

934
01:00:19.650 --> 01:00:21.594
Right.

935
01:00:21.618 --> 01:00:28.001
Look. Michael. you and I have fun together.
But this is not real.

936
01:00:28.025 --> 01:00:32.529
You know. I can't risk
what I have with Hugh.

937
01:00:33.330 --> 01:00:34.765
I just can't.

938
01:00:35.565 --> 01:00:37.243
He's my future.

939
01:00:37.267 --> 01:00:39.569
Yeah. you already said that.
Well. I'm saying it again.

940
01:00:40.738 --> 01:00:43.249
And this is all very
easy for you. you know?

941
01:00:43.273 --> 01:00:46.019
You have no consequences here.

942
01:00:46.043 --> 01:00:48.779
I get it. No. No. you don't.

943
01:00:50.815 --> 01:00:52.817
You know. this is my life.

944
01:00:53.818 --> 01:00:56.020
Okay? I have responsibilities.

945
01:00:57.621 --> 01:01:01.091
I'm not this little girl anymore
with an imaginary friend.

946
01:01:06.296 --> 01:01:07.597
I grew up.

947
01:01:10.567 --> 01:01:12.970
Everybody has to
grow up. Michael.

948
01:01:14.571 --> 01:01:16.206
Everybody but you.

949
01:01:25.449 --> 01:01:29.429
I haven't seen her in three days.
I miss her so much.

950
01:01:29.453 --> 01:01:31.531
We don't miss our kids.
We care for them.

951
01:01:31.555 --> 01:01:33.700
help them be their best
selves and then we leave.

952
01:01:33.724 --> 01:01:35.468
I know. I know. I just
wanna make her happy.

953
01:01:35.492 --> 01:01:37.971
It isn't your job
to make her happy.

954
01:01:37.995 --> 01:01:41.074
I wish I could stay. you know.
and be a part of her life.

955
01:01:41.098 --> 01:01:42.508
I could learn to
live in her world.

956
01:01:42.532 --> 01:01:44.277
take on responsibilities
and be a grown up.

957
01:01:44.301 --> 01:01:46.079
Have you lost your mind?

958
01:01:46.103 --> 01:01:49.249
No! I only have until her birthday
to show her I've changed.

959
01:01:49.273 --> 01:01:53.653
This isn't about you. She's happy. She's
getting married. Your job is done.

960
01:01:53.677 --> 01:01:54.821
Just go home.

961
01:01:54.845 --> 01:01:56.689
But... No "buts." Michael.

962
01:01:56.713 --> 01:02:00.861
If you don't show up at an exit station
the moment you're supposed to leave.

963
01:02:00.885 --> 01:02:02.462
who knows what could happen?

964
01:02:02.486 --> 01:02:05.389
You could disappear.
cease to exist.

965
01:02:06.290 --> 01:02:08.735
Don't do it.

966
01:02:08.759 --> 01:02:11.504
I don't have a lot of experience.
but I'm great with people.

967
01:02:11.528 --> 01:02:13.673
I'm trustworthy. and I'm
there when you need me.

968
01:02:13.697 --> 01:02:15.508
So why do you wanna work here?

969
01:02:15.532 --> 01:02:18.111
I like food. and it's the
responsible thing to do.

970
01:02:18.135 --> 01:02:19.880
That's a good answer.

971
01:02:19.904 --> 01:02:22.704
That's more than I can say about my
prima donna head chef there. Gerard.

972
01:02:22.728 --> 01:02:24.830
Comes in late. attitude sucks.

973
01:02:25.275 --> 01:02:26.652
(SIGHS)

974
01:02:26.676 --> 01:02:29.389
Can you wash dishes? Yeah.

975
01:02:29.413 --> 01:02:32.959
I'm just glad that you finally
realized that your friend.

976
01:02:32.983 --> 01:02:34.961
Michael. was just using you.

977
01:02:34.985 --> 01:02:38.164
Well. I don't think he
was using me. per se.

978
01:02:38.188 --> 01:02:40.433
Okay. whatever.

979
01:02:40.457 --> 01:02:43.693
Look. it was great to see him. but
it was time for him to go home.

980
01:02:44.528 --> 01:02:45.796
I agree.

981
01:02:47.131 --> 01:02:52.036
So. I think I wanna write again.

982
01:02:54.238 --> 01:02:56.082
Writing what?

983
01:02:56.106 --> 01:02:57.183
I don't know.

984
01:02:57.207 --> 01:02:59.409
Maybe a children's
story or something.

985
01:03:01.711 --> 01:03:05.058
Honey. I know what this is.
What?

986
01:03:05.082 --> 01:03:08.394
Well. I was almost nominated
for a Tony Award.

987
01:03:08.418 --> 01:03:10.931
and I'm gonna be in a big movie.

988
01:03:10.955 --> 01:03:13.666
and. you know. my book's
gonna be a bestseller.

989
01:03:13.690 --> 01:03:15.601
It's okay for you to
feel a little insecure.

990
01:03:15.625 --> 01:03:19.672
No. that's not what it is at all. I
just always wanted to be a writer.

991
01:03:19.696 --> 01:03:21.774
Well. you never
mentioned it before.

992
01:03:21.798 --> 01:03:24.477
When I was 10 years old. I decided
that I wanted to be a writer.

993
01:03:24.501 --> 01:03:28.748
but then fear and judgment got
in the way as I grew older.

994
01:03:28.772 --> 01:03:30.783
and now... I remember
when I was 10.

995
01:03:30.807 --> 01:03:32.819
I had a dream.

996
01:03:32.843 --> 01:03:35.779
I wanted to be president of
the Screen Actors Guild.

997
01:03:37.314 --> 01:03:39.259
Are you getting sick?

998
01:03:39.283 --> 01:03:42.028
No. but if I were. wouldn't
you want to take care of me?

999
01:03:42.052 --> 01:03:44.321
And risk both of us being sick?

1000
01:03:48.525 --> 01:03:49.793
You ever missed a girl?

1001
01:03:50.928 --> 01:03:53.130
I mean. really missed her.

1002
01:03:54.932 --> 01:03:56.642
Right.

1003
01:03:56.666 --> 01:04:02.839
She's just so pretty. but
beautiful and fun and cool.

1004
01:04:07.277 --> 01:04:09.489
So where is this fun girl. huh?

1005
01:04:09.513 --> 01:04:12.358
I don't know. Not a
little girl anymore.

1006
01:04:12.382 --> 01:04:15.585
You know. she goes places
and she does stuff.

1007
01:04:18.722 --> 01:04:21.134
I'll have another one.

1008
01:04:21.158 --> 01:04:22.598
I think maybe you've
had enough. huh?

1009
01:04:23.760 --> 01:04:24.861
Okay.

1010
01:04:28.865 --> 01:04:30.944
Maybe you should call this girl.

1011
01:04:30.968 --> 01:04:32.436
tell her how you feel.

1012
01:04:42.146 --> 01:04:45.125
Hi. Jane. it's Michael.

1013
01:04:45.149 --> 01:04:49.186
I got a job washing dishes at
Sam's Restaurant and Bar in SoHo.

1014
01:04:51.255 --> 01:04:53.690
I just wanted to
call and say hi.

1015
01:04:54.791 --> 01:04:56.693
see how you were doing.

1016
01:04:58.362 --> 01:04:59.729
I miss you.

1017
01:05:04.101 --> 01:05:06.170
Hi. Jane. it's Michael.

1018
01:05:13.743 --> 01:05:14.854
What is this?

1019
01:05:14.878 --> 01:05:17.347
It's macaroni and cheese and...

1020
01:05:20.084 --> 01:05:21.794
Rice Krispies treats.

1021
01:05:21.818 --> 01:05:22.895
Is this a joke?

1022
01:05:22.919 --> 01:05:24.530
No. it's comfort food.

1023
01:05:24.554 --> 01:05:26.666
No. this is sugar.
and this is carbs.

1024
01:05:26.690 --> 01:05:29.402
I can't eat this. I got
to stay in shape. I know.

1025
01:05:29.426 --> 01:05:33.597
I'm auditioning for a feature film. It's
the most important time in my life.

1026
01:05:34.731 --> 01:05:37.034
And marrying you.

1027
01:05:42.506 --> 01:05:45.318
You know what? It's fine.
It's fine. Look.

1028
01:05:45.342 --> 01:05:47.377
What harm could a few
carbs do. right?

1029
01:05:49.479 --> 01:05:51.015
I'm not that hungry anyway.

1030
01:05:56.753 --> 01:05:58.553
Do you want to go outside
and build a snowman?

1031
01:05:59.223 --> 01:06:00.433
It's 20 degrees.

1032
01:06:00.457 --> 01:06:02.468
You wanna go outside
and build a snowman?

1033
01:06:02.492 --> 01:06:04.704
Are you kidding? No.

1034
01:06:04.728 --> 01:06:06.973
It'll be fun.

1035
01:06:06.997 --> 01:06:09.317
This is the kind of stuff you
and Michael used to do. right?

1036
01:06:10.934 --> 01:06:12.069
I just want to be happy.

1037
01:06:17.441 --> 01:06:18.508
We are happy.

1038
01:06:20.110 --> 01:06:22.512
We have everything that we want.

1039
01:06:23.913 --> 01:06:26.116
This is what happy looks like.

1040
01:06:33.757 --> 01:06:36.269
I still have no idea what
to get Hugh for Christmas.

1041
01:06:36.293 --> 01:06:37.670
What's he getting you?

1042
01:06:37.694 --> 01:06:41.407
Skis. We're going to Colorado.
skiing for our honeymoon.

1043
01:06:41.431 --> 01:06:43.476
You hate to ski.

1044
01:06:43.500 --> 01:06:45.935
Well. not completely
and totally.

1045
01:06:49.906 --> 01:06:52.818
Michael would love this scarf.

1046
01:06:52.842 --> 01:06:55.362
I'm gonna get it for him. I thought
you didn't know where he was.

1047
01:06:56.946 --> 01:06:58.915
He left me a message
telling me where he works.

1048
01:07:00.817 --> 01:07:03.129
You have no idea what to
get Hugh for Christmas.

1049
01:07:03.153 --> 01:07:05.565
yet Michael. no problem.

1050
01:07:05.589 --> 01:07:08.501
You should go see him.
tell him how you feel.

1051
01:07:08.525 --> 01:07:11.604
No. that's not fair to Hugh. I'll
just send the scarf to Michael.

1052
01:07:11.628 --> 01:07:15.799
Fair? Hugh is in California
surrounded by beautiful actresses.

1053
01:07:16.400 --> 01:07:18.311
So?

1054
01:07:18.335 --> 01:07:21.171
So nothing. I'm just saying...

1055
01:07:27.177 --> 01:07:32.825
Excuse me. Excuse me. Hi.

1056
01:07:32.849 --> 01:07:34.609
I was hoping you could
help me with something.

1057
01:07:34.633 --> 01:07:36.096
It's gonna be about
an hour wait.

1058
01:07:36.120 --> 01:07:40.032
Sorry. Christmas special. We're giving
out free cookies with every meal.

1059
01:07:40.056 --> 01:07:41.901
I'm actually looking
for someone.

1060
01:07:41.925 --> 01:07:44.804
His name is Michael. I think
he's the dishwasher here.

1061
01:07:44.828 --> 01:07:46.196
You mean Michael. the chef?

1062
01:07:48.698 --> 01:07:50.567
Jane. Yeah.

1063
01:07:52.269 --> 01:07:53.779
You're Jane?

1064
01:07:53.803 --> 01:07:54.938
Yeah.

1065
01:07:55.872 --> 01:07:57.207
That Jane?

1066
01:07:59.443 --> 01:08:03.247
Yeah. I guess so. Thank you.

1067
01:08:04.348 --> 01:08:06.716
Jane. hey.

1068
01:08:07.217 --> 01:08:08.952
Hi. Hi.

1069
01:08:11.355 --> 01:08:13.899
I just wanted to stop by
and see how you're doing.

1070
01:08:13.923 --> 01:08:16.226
Yeah. well. let's grab a seat.
Okay.

1071
01:08:20.096 --> 01:08:23.509
I brought you a little
Christmas present.

1072
01:08:23.533 --> 01:08:25.169
Thank you. Yeah.

1073
01:08:27.036 --> 01:08:30.483
I love it. This is great.

1074
01:08:30.507 --> 01:08:32.576
How are you? I'm well.

1075
01:08:34.911 --> 01:08:36.722
Look at you.

1076
01:08:36.746 --> 01:08:38.758
You're this huge success.

1077
01:08:38.782 --> 01:08:41.494
Well. thanks to you.

1078
01:08:41.518 --> 01:08:43.629
The chef quit. so I
took your suggestion.

1079
01:08:43.653 --> 01:08:45.231
My suggestion? Yeah.

1080
01:08:45.255 --> 01:08:47.575
You said you'd rather eat mac
and cheese than anything else.

1081
01:08:47.599 --> 01:08:51.904
so I made mac and cheese. grilled
cheese. tomato soup. Tater Tots.

1082
01:08:51.928 --> 01:08:53.939
Those were my favorite
foods when I was little.

1083
01:08:53.963 --> 01:08:55.775
I know. They're every
kid's favorite foods.

1084
01:08:55.799 --> 01:08:58.668
It turns out people like to be
reminded of their childhood.

1085
01:09:00.837 --> 01:09:02.882
Michael. hi. Hey.

1086
01:09:02.906 --> 01:09:05.718
The girls certainly do love you.

1087
01:09:05.742 --> 01:09:07.076
You'll always be my girl.

1088
01:09:09.646 --> 01:09:13.226
How's Hugh? He's great.
He's great.

1089
01:09:13.250 --> 01:09:16.986
The wedding's coming up soon. He
flew to California for an audition.

1090
01:09:17.754 --> 01:09:19.232
Really?

1091
01:09:19.256 --> 01:09:21.234
He'll be back in time
for the wedding.

1092
01:09:21.258 --> 01:09:23.536
Okay. so the wedding's still on.

1093
01:09:23.560 --> 01:09:26.606
Michael. are you coming
out for drinks later?

1094
01:09:26.630 --> 01:09:28.432
Yeah. I'll be there.

1095
01:09:29.065 --> 01:09:30.376
Fun.

1096
01:09:30.400 --> 01:09:33.879
Yeah. we all go for drinks
at this place after work.

1097
01:09:33.903 --> 01:09:35.372
You should come with us.

1098
01:09:39.643 --> 01:09:40.977
It's late.

1099
01:09:42.612 --> 01:09:45.081
I should go home. No. right.
Right.

1100
01:09:46.082 --> 01:09:48.618
Well. it was great to see you.

1101
01:09:51.288 --> 01:09:52.832
You. too.

1102
01:09:52.856 --> 01:09:54.700
I'm really happy for you.

1103
01:09:54.724 --> 01:09:55.759
Thank you.

1104
01:09:57.126 --> 01:09:59.128
Am I gonna see you again?

1105
01:10:01.465 --> 01:10:04.901
I don't know. You
know. I hope so.

1106
01:10:09.439 --> 01:10:10.974
Merry Christmas. Jane.

1107
01:10:16.079 --> 01:10:17.447
Merry Christmas. Michael.

1108
01:10:21.585 --> 01:10:23.052
Got you last.

1109
01:10:25.855 --> 01:10:27.324
Got you last.

1110
01:11:25.014 --> 01:11:29.586
After you left. I used to spend
hours thinking about you.

1111
01:11:32.389 --> 01:11:38.328
I just kept looking for you. and I
kept hoping that you would come back.

1112
01:11:40.029 --> 01:11:41.531
At some point.

1113
01:11:42.999 --> 01:11:47.103
it just became too painful
to think about you anymore.

1114
01:11:50.106 --> 01:11:53.443
so I just pretended that you
weren't important to me.

1115
01:11:56.880 --> 01:11:58.482
And I shut down.

1116
01:12:01.785 --> 01:12:05.889
It's easier not to feel
anything about anything.

1117
01:12:12.562 --> 01:12:15.131
But I don't want to
do that anymore.

1118
01:12:18.368 --> 01:12:20.870
I want to lie here
with you forever.

1119
01:12:24.107 --> 01:12:25.709
I love you. Jane.

1120
01:12:42.892 --> 01:12:44.127
Michael?

1121
01:13:15.358 --> 01:13:17.403
Hi. Hi. Hey.

1122
01:13:17.427 --> 01:13:19.605
Got us some breakfast.

1123
01:13:19.629 --> 01:13:20.964
I thought you left.

1124
01:13:21.765 --> 01:13:24.000
I think we should talk.

1125
01:13:25.268 --> 01:13:26.979
Later.

1126
01:13:27.003 --> 01:13:28.714
There's something I
have to tell you.

1127
01:13:28.738 --> 01:13:29.939
I already know.

1128
01:13:31.107 --> 01:13:32.618
You do?

1129
01:13:32.642 --> 01:13:34.578
Yeah. and I love you. too.

1130
01:13:36.713 --> 01:13:37.914
Come on.

1131
01:13:41.818 --> 01:13:44.954
These have been the most
perfect days of my life.

1132
01:13:46.089 --> 01:13:47.390
Mine. too.

1133
01:13:49.593 --> 01:13:51.895
What? What is it?

1134
01:13:58.968 --> 01:14:00.937
I have to go back. Jane.

1135
01:14:02.872 --> 01:14:03.983
You're leaving?

1136
01:14:04.007 --> 01:14:05.117
I don't want to.

1137
01:14:05.141 --> 01:14:06.185
Then don't.

1138
01:14:06.209 --> 01:14:07.677
I have to. I don't
have a choice.

1139
01:14:10.179 --> 01:14:12.091
Why did you do this?

1140
01:14:12.115 --> 01:14:15.828
Why did you come here and build
this life for yourself here?

1141
01:14:15.852 --> 01:14:21.024
Why did you let me fall in love with
you when you knew you were leaving?

1142
01:14:22.726 --> 01:14:24.003
Michael. I trusted you.

1143
01:14:24.027 --> 01:14:29.341
Jane. falling in love with
you has been the best.

1144
01:14:29.365 --> 01:14:31.925
the best thing I've ever experienced.
You don't know what love is.

1145
01:14:31.949 --> 01:14:33.993
otherwise you wouldn't
be leaving me right now.

1146
01:14:34.017 --> 01:14:35.515
Jane... No.

1147
01:14:35.539 --> 01:14:37.874
The first time that you left me.

1148
01:14:39.576 --> 01:14:42.211
I swore that I would
never forget you.

1149
01:14:44.581 --> 01:14:48.327
This time. I promise you

1150
01:14:48.351 --> 01:14:52.889
I will not spend one more moment
of my life thinking about you.

1151
01:14:57.160 --> 01:14:59.629
I don't ever want
to see you again.

1152
01:15:12.676 --> 01:15:14.410
God. I feel like I'm dying.

1153
01:15:15.545 --> 01:15:19.749
You're not dying.
It's a broken heart.

1154
01:15:20.584 --> 01:15:22.427
Why does it hurt so much?

1155
01:15:22.451 --> 01:15:25.254
It just means you're human.

1156
01:15:55.051 --> 01:15:57.029
Owen.

1157
01:15:57.053 --> 01:16:00.800
I want you to make sure that every guest
gets one of these theater schedules.

1158
01:16:00.824 --> 01:16:02.784
People always like something
to read during dinner.

1159
01:16:03.426 --> 01:16:07.707
Why. you're early. Oh. God.

1160
01:16:07.731 --> 01:16:09.474
I'm sorry. People magazine.

1161
01:16:09.498 --> 01:16:12.477
Welcome. welcome. I'm
Vivian Claremont.

1162
01:16:12.501 --> 01:16:14.980
mother of the bride and owner
of the Claremont Theater.

1163
01:16:15.004 --> 01:16:16.315
where the groom. Hugh Morrison.

1164
01:16:16.339 --> 01:16:18.383
is currently performing
in Barrymore Speaks.

1165
01:16:18.407 --> 01:16:22.054
Tuesday through Saturday
and two shows on Sunday.

1166
01:16:22.078 --> 01:16:25.381
Darren. make sure he has a
good seat right up front.

1167
01:16:26.683 --> 01:16:29.152
No. no. No carnations.
More roses.

1168
01:16:29.653 --> 01:16:30.830
Thank you.

1169
01:16:30.854 --> 01:16:32.665
You sure you want to do this?

1170
01:16:32.689 --> 01:16:34.133
Of course.

1171
01:16:34.157 --> 01:16:37.269
It's not too late. you know.
You can still walk away.

1172
01:16:37.293 --> 01:16:40.429
No. this is the right decision.

1173
01:16:41.364 --> 01:16:42.942
Hugh is a good man.

1174
01:16:42.966 --> 01:16:45.344
Darling. you look beautiful.

1175
01:16:45.368 --> 01:16:47.379
Thank you. So do you.

1176
01:16:47.403 --> 01:16:52.017
I know. It's going to be a perfect
Christmas Eve wedding in New York City.

1177
01:16:52.041 --> 01:16:54.486
And the place is
crawling with paparazzi.

1178
01:16:54.510 --> 01:16:56.612
Jackie. is that for me?

1179
01:16:58.581 --> 01:17:01.084
Cheers. everyone. ALL: Cheers.

1180
01:18:01.978 --> 01:18:05.281
The right choice isn't always
the best choice. Jane.

1181
01:18:36.612 --> 01:18:39.916
You look so beautiful.
Thank you.

1182
01:18:46.322 --> 01:18:49.301
I can't wait for our honeymoon.

1183
01:18:49.325 --> 01:18:52.395
New Year's on the slopes.
I'm so excited.

1184
01:18:53.496 --> 01:18:54.597
I don't like to ski.

1185
01:18:57.200 --> 01:19:01.080
Sure you do. No. No. I don't.

1186
01:19:01.104 --> 01:19:02.948
You don't?

1187
01:19:02.972 --> 01:19:04.172
You never told me that before.

1188
01:19:04.196 --> 01:19:07.633
Yeah. I did. You
just didn't listen.

1189
01:19:15.919 --> 01:19:18.163
What's my favorite color?

1190
01:19:18.187 --> 01:19:19.989
Now? Yes. right now.

1191
01:19:21.090 --> 01:19:22.234
Blue.

1192
01:19:22.258 --> 01:19:24.069
No. that's your favorite color.

1193
01:19:24.093 --> 01:19:26.671
What's my favorite flower?

1194
01:19:26.695 --> 01:19:28.540
Orchid. No.

1195
01:19:28.564 --> 01:19:33.745
You always send me orchids. but. really.
that's your mother's favorite flower.

1196
01:19:33.769 --> 01:19:38.141
My favorite are yellow roses.
And Michael knew that.

1197
01:19:43.012 --> 01:19:44.756
That's what this is about?

1198
01:19:44.780 --> 01:19:47.359
Listen. Michael's not here.
I am.

1199
01:19:47.383 --> 01:19:52.297
No. it's not about Michael. Michael's gone.
It's about you and me.

1200
01:19:52.321 --> 01:19:56.268
Look. I forgive you. okay?

1201
01:19:56.292 --> 01:19:59.896
For the whole Michael thing.
I wasn't perfect. either.

1202
01:20:03.199 --> 01:20:05.001
Let's just get married.

1203
01:20:05.869 --> 01:20:07.403
Let's get married.

1204
01:20:08.637 --> 01:20:11.350
I can't do this. What?

1205
01:20:11.374 --> 01:20:14.153
I'm sorry. What? What?

1206
01:20:14.177 --> 01:20:16.521
I know what love feels
like. and this is not it.

1207
01:20:16.545 --> 01:20:17.823
Jane. Jane...

1208
01:20:17.847 --> 01:20:19.647
Where are you going? I
don't love him. Mother.

1209
01:20:19.671 --> 01:20:21.393
You love him enough.
It's not enough.

1210
01:20:21.417 --> 01:20:24.696
This may be your last chance
for happiness and security.

1211
01:20:24.720 --> 01:20:25.831
I have to find Michael.

1212
01:20:25.855 --> 01:20:27.299
Jane.

1213
01:20:27.323 --> 01:20:29.283
If you do this. you'll be
ruining this day forever.

1214
01:20:29.307 --> 01:20:32.911
Christmas Eve. your birthday. will always
be the day that you ruined your life.

1215
01:20:34.063 --> 01:20:35.740
Jane.

1216
01:20:35.764 --> 01:20:38.434
My birthday. What time is it?

1217
01:20:40.236 --> 01:20:41.780
I got to go.

1218
01:20:41.804 --> 01:20:44.283
Fifteen minutes till
the moment I was born!

1219
01:20:44.307 --> 01:20:45.774
But I'm gonna be a big star.

1220
01:21:14.637 --> 01:21:18.307
Here. Merry Christmas!
What do I do with these?

1221
01:21:22.912 --> 01:21:25.490
That's a great choice.

1222
01:21:25.514 --> 01:21:28.817
Thank you so much. You're welcome.
Happy holidays.

1223
01:21:34.123 --> 01:21:36.025
Can I help you. sir?

1224
01:21:40.196 --> 01:21:42.298
No. thank you.

1225
01:21:44.233 --> 01:21:45.701
I'm done here.

1226
01:21:59.582 --> 01:22:00.816
Michael!

1227
01:22:07.623 --> 01:22:09.358
I love you so much.

1228
01:22:10.726 --> 01:22:12.561
I've always loved you.

1229
01:22:14.797 --> 01:22:18.734
You are my soul mate.
my one true love.

1230
01:22:20.936 --> 01:22:23.983
I've always loved you. too.

1231
01:22:24.007 --> 01:22:29.345
Loving you has been the
best part of my life.

1232
01:22:32.215 --> 01:22:34.517
and I'm gonna miss you forever.

1233
01:22:36.219 --> 01:22:37.286
Stay with me.

1234
01:22:37.820 --> 01:22:38.988
I can't.

1235
01:22:41.090 --> 01:22:43.459
What am I supposed
to do without you?

1236
01:24:00.469 --> 01:24:02.771
They're perfect for each other.

1237
01:24:08.611 --> 01:24:11.323
Michael?

1238
01:24:11.347 --> 01:24:14.583
She's an Olympic swimmer. and
he's an underwater tuba player.

1239
01:24:16.919 --> 01:24:18.187
I thought you had to leave.

1240
01:24:19.422 --> 01:24:20.923
I couldn't go.

1241
01:24:22.825 --> 01:24:24.769
I don't understand.

1242
01:24:24.793 --> 01:24:29.064
When you were a little girl. I
came to you because you needed me.

1243
01:24:32.435 --> 01:24:36.715
I came back because I need you.

1244
01:24:36.739 --> 01:24:38.507
I don't exist without you.

1245
01:24:43.179 --> 01:24:44.280
What about the rules?

1246
01:24:46.315 --> 01:24:48.151
Some rules were
made to be broken.

1247
01:24:52.221 --> 01:24:54.433
I wanted to get you something

1248
01:24:54.457 --> 01:24:58.927
that is as special and
unique as you are.

1249
01:25:04.433 --> 01:25:06.034
That is my ring.

1250
01:25:20.683 --> 01:25:22.084
I love you. Michael.

1251
01:25:24.019 --> 01:25:25.621
I love you. Jane.

1252
01:25:29.892 --> 01:25:32.528
Did you say an
underwater tuba player?

1253
01:25:34.830 --> 01:25:36.565
Would I make that up?

1254
01:25:39.402 --> 01:25:40.812
And then what happened?

1255
01:25:40.836 --> 01:25:44.449
Well. she met him when she
fell off a cruise ship.

1256
01:25:44.473 --> 01:25:46.885
That's how they met. She
was doing a high dive.

1257
01:25:46.909 --> 01:25:48.844
and she overshot the pool.

1257
